title: fruit dip
directions: Combine until smooth.
Serve as dip for fresh fruit.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Combine the remaining ingredients except the crumbs and fold in the egg whites.
Transfer to a greased 1-quart souffle dish and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dream square pie
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Prepare Dream Whip with 1 cup of milk as directed on package.
I use a large bowl. Add the pudding and the remaining 1 3/4 cups milk.
Blend at high speed for 2 minutes.
Dice the oranges and fold into the mixture. Add nuts.
Spoon half of mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Spoon the rest of the mixture over them.
Garnish with nuts.

title: "almost" no-fat pasta dinner
directions: Cook spaghetti until done; drain.
Cook vegetables until tender-crisp; drain.
If using chicken, may grill or broil or boil, if desired.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve warm or cold.
Delicious and practically fat-free.

title: skillet hash
directions: Fry potatoes until done, drain off grease and add chopped onion and can of corned beef.
Cover and cook slowly for a few minutes.

title: brunch dish
directions: Put 6 slices of bread in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Put on 1/2 of the ham and cheese.
Then 6 slices of bread, ham and cheese. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mash cheese with a fork.
Beat egg yolks; add to cheese.
Stir in other ingredients.
Beat with a beater until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a moderate oven until brown.
A knife will come out clean when inserted in center.

title: checkerboard masterpiece(fun to make, but a little tricky)
directions: Sift flour.
Measure
and
resift
times with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter.
Mix in sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat
until
smooth and fluffy.
Add vanilla and stir in flour mixture
in
several
portions until smooth.
Divide mixture in 2 portions
and mix melted cooled chocolate with 1 portion.
Line a small bread loaf pan or refrigerator freezing tray with wax paper.
Pack
the chocolate dough into the bottom in a uniform
layer.
Place in refrigerator until very firm, then cover this
with half the plain dough, then repeat chilling and add another
layer
of chocolate and finally the last of plain
dough. Try
to
keep
the
layers
uniform
in thickness and
smooth. Cover
with
wax paper and chill overnight in the refrigerator. Turn the layered loaf out onto wax paper on a
molding
board
and cut into uniform thick slices, using a
thin
sharp
knife.

title: barbecue chipped ham
directions: Combine all the ingredients but the chipped ham and bring to boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Then add chipped ham.
Cook for 5 more minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs; add all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter in baking dish (2 quart casserole) or iron skillet, sprinkle
of cheese over, add rest of batter and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Add water to raisins and boil 5 minutes. Cool. Stir in soda and let stand. Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add raisin mixture.
Add dry ingredients. Bake on greased cookie sheets at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Add coconut. Toss to mix.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with curry or sweet and sour pork.

title: sam's m&m cookies
directions: Coarsely chop M&M's (1 1/2 cups).
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and mix. Stir in candy and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from oven; decorate with remaining M&M's.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain and add catsup; cover.
Simmer for about 10 minutes on low.

title: date bites
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap 1/3 slice around each date. Secure with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
(Can be done in microwave.)

title: fudge
directions: Use a heavy pan; add sugar, cream and marshmallows.
Cook 8 minutes after boiling.
In mixing bowl, add chocolate chips, butter, nuts and vanilla.
Pour sugar mixture over ingredients in bowl.
Pour immediately into greased and buttered 10-inch baking dish.

title: cheese hash brown dish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour over hash browns.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: baked pineapple with cheese
directions: Drain pineapple; keep 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine flour and sugar and stir in reserved juice.
Add shredded cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix well.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole dish that has been greased.
Combine margarine and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: homemade banana cake
directions: Blend together sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix in flour and beat well. Add bananas.
Mix water with baking soda and add to the batter.
Put in the baking powder and mix well.
Pour batter into two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: gelatin poke cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend; then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin as directed on package.
Poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour warm gelatin over cake.
Chill at least four hours.
Spread prepared Dream Whip whipped topping over cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, pork, bread crumbs and onion.
Mix separately the mustard, egg, brown sugar, ginger, thyme and vinegar.
Pour into hamburger mixture and blend with a wooden spoon.
Can be baked in a loaf pan or casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes, then, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan; spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread even in layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put butter on top. Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: Steam raisins in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell.
Top with sugar.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Toss in marshmallows and coconut. Fold in sour cream.
(Add 2 teaspoons sugar if desired.) Refrigerate.

title: chess squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in pan (9 x 13-inch baking dish).
Mix 2 eggs with cake mix.
Put on top of melted butter. Pour pecans over cake mixture.
Mix powdered sugar with cream cheese and 3 beaten eggs.
Pour over nuts.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In 1 quart glass measure with handle, combine chips, milk and salt.
Cook on HI for 3 minutes or until chips melt; stirring after each 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into aluminum foil-lined 8 or 9 inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 2 lbs.

title: turkey breast with onion gravy
directions: Thaw turkey.
Rinse under water and dry with paper towels. Salt both sides with seasoned salt.
Place in crock-pot.
Add onion soup and 1/4 to 1/2 can of water.
Cover and cook on high setting 6 1/2 to 7 hours until fork-tender.
Remove turkey.
Add thickening made with water and flour and a little pepper.
Cook about 10 minutes or until gravy is thickened.

title: sweet potatoes and corned beef
directions: Boil sweet potatoes and smash them when done.
Make balls and stuff with corned beef.
Cover balls with eggs and bread crumbs twice.
Fry sweet potato balls in vegetable oil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Place oil in saucepan.
Saute onions until transparent.
Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, sugar, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle Parmesan, if desired.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add diced potato and eggs; scramble all together.
Place generous amount of cooked mixture in a steamed tortilla.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas in a large bowl.
Add soda, sugar, eggs, butter and flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Black walnuts are optional.

title: broccoli egg puff
directions: Cut off broccoli buds.
Set aside.
Chop remaining stalk. Cook, uncovered, in small amount of boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Add reserved buds; cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside. In small mixing bowl, beat eggs.
With a wire whisk or rotary beater, beat in flour mixture.
Stir in cottage cheese and bacon. Evenly spread broccoli in bottom of a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour egg mixture evenly over broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar or Swiss cheese.
Bake 3 minutes more or until center is almost set and cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: burro pie
directions: Fry shells in butter, both sides.
Cook onion, beef, beans and sauce together in frying pan.
Put layer of sauce in bottom of casserole dish, then shells and cheese, ground beef mixture and continue layers until all is used, topping with cheese.
It is best made ahead two to three hours, then covered and bake in microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: road side potatoes
directions: Combine the potatoes, cheese and melted butter.
Place in a well buttered 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add half and half.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are slightly crusty on the edges and lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, grated cheese and pimentos.
Pour over asparagus in casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine; put on top.
Cook in oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, pickle, eggs, pimento and green peppers.
Blend mayonnaise with mustard and sweet pickle juice.
Mix mayonnaise mixture with potatoes until well coated. Add remaining ingredients.
Garnish with additional egg slices. Chill.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs; add potatoes.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at
325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: salmon corn cakes or tuna corn cakes
directions: Grease heated skillet, if necessary.
Mix eggs, flour, lemon juice, salt and pepper with hand beater until foamy.
Stir in corn and salmon (tuna).

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into small pieces.
Mix ingredients and sprinkle on top.

title: hot sausage squares
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Drain well and cool.
Add next 4 ingredients.
(This may be made day before.) Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish with crescent roll dough.
Press to seal perforations.
Bake about 2 minutes just until set.
Sprinkle with cooked cooled sausage.
Combine egg mixture and pour over sausage.
Sprinkle with about 4 or 5 slices of lite American cheese broken up.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cut into squares.

title: braised beef
directions: Cut stew beef in small cubes.
Dice onion and celery and put into big pot.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce, also add water.
Cook on high for 1/2 hour.
Then cook on medium for about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve with noodles or rice or over mashed potatoes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add remaining ingredients except kidney beans, close cover securely.
Cook in pressure cooker for 5 minutes.
Let pressure drop of its own accord.
Add kidney beans and heat through.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Store for 12 hours in airtight container.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in airtight container.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water with jello.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Chill.
Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Add nuts, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on jello.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: sweet surrender salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and gently fold together.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: easy cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add vanilla and cheese. Beat until smooth.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until brown on sides.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: cavatini(large quantity)
directions: Cook 1 to 2 cups each of 3 different pastas; drain and set aside.
Brown and drain sausage, pepperoni, onions and green pepper.
Mix pastas, meats, onions and green pepper.
Stir in mushroom pieces, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Stir well.
Put in a lasagna pan or roast pan and bake at 350° until hot; stir once or twice.
Remove from oven and sprinkle shredded cheese over top.
Put back into oven until cheese melts. Serve in pan.
Quick for large group.
Enjoy.

title: chicken parmesan(low-fat)
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Drain.
Combine tomatoes, arrowroot, oregano and pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Pour heated sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese. Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Line cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt butterscotch chips and chocolate chips until smooth, stirring constantly.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into freezer can; fill with milk and freeze.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine dressing, apricot preserves, water and soup mix and stir.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove cover.
Add pineapple and bake for 1/2 hour more uncovered. Delicious!!

title: potato pancakes
directions: Boil, then drain and mash potatoes.
Beat egg in small bowl. Mix all other ingredients, except oil.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over low heat.
Shape potato mixture into 8 patties. Place in oil; fry until golden brown, turning once.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix.
Bake in oven for 5 hours at 275°.
Do not stir while cooking.

title: hamburger cups
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all ingredients except cheese and biscuits.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Press biscuits in a cupcake pan to form cup.
Fill each cup 2/3 full with meat mixture.
Put oven on 350° and cook until biscuits are golden brown.
Grate cheese and put on cups while warm.
Serve.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, and sugar in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix beaten egg with orange juice, rind, butter, and hot water.
Fold flour mixture into egg mixture until blended.
Do not beat.
Gently fold in cranberries and walnuts. Spoon into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: eldorado casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion salt.
Add black olives, then add tomato sauce.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and green chilies. Mash chips.
Layer chips, sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and melted butter.
Add milk, salt, pepper, chicken, onion and pimento.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spoon 1 cup of chicken mixture into center of each rectangle.
Pull up corners; pinch to seal. Brush top with melted butter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a heavy skillet, melt margarine.
Add flour and stir a minute or two.
Add milk to make gravy.
When thickened, add cocoa mixed in the water and sugar.
Stir until mixed well.
Add vanilla last.
Serve over biscuits or fried potatoes.

title: hillbilly vegetable soup
directions: In a heavy, large pot (this makes a lot of soup), add shredded cabbage.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
When cabbage becomes transparent, add potatoes; continue cooking until potatoes are almost soft.
Add corn, tomatoes, okra and lima beans.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add broccoli; simmer 30 minutes more.
Note: You can add other vegetables or some leftover dried beans (beans only, not broth).
Add water for thinner or thicker soup.

title: california pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Dice all vegetables.
Drain sliced olives.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pork chop delight
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Combine soup and milk.
Place pork chops, potatoes and carrots in a slow cooker.
Pour soup mixture all over.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and cornflakes, and put in a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter and mix with cornflakes or bread crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Steam broccoli.
Thoroughly squeeze out all water.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to broccoli.
Place in baking dish or pan and spread top with grated cheese (small amount).
Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes. Children will enjoy.

title: spicy seven layer dip
directions: Coat bottom of pie plate with refried beans.
Brown ground beef in skillet; add chorizo when meat is brown.
Layer meat mixture on top of refried beans.
Add single layer of sliced olives.
Coat olives with layer of guacamole.
Next, add layer of sour cream.
Top with grated Jack and Cheddar cheese.
Chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: frozen mint dessert
directions: Crush the mints.
Whip the cream and fold in mints.
Crush Hydrox cookies; add butter and powdered sugar.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Save some to sprinkle on top.
Spread on cream and mint mixture.
Sprinkle top with remaining cookie crumbs. Freeze until hard.
Make the day before you need it.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Dress with Italian dressing and marinate a few hours in refrigerator.

title: crunch-top apple pie
directions: Arrange sliced apples in pie crust.
Combine sugar, graham cracker crumbs, flour, walnuts and cinnamon; spread over apples. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° until crust is browned and apples are tender when pierced (about 1 hour).
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix soup and Miracle Whip together.
Spread a casserole dish with Pam spray.
Layer in this order:
1/2 the broccoli, 1/2 the eggs, 1/2 the pimentos and 1/2 the soup mixture. Repeat layers.
Saute the bread cubes in the margarine until lightly browned and place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: german chocolate cake topping
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a skillet.
Cook 15 minutes stirring continually.
Add pecans and coconut.
Stir until cool and thick enough to spread.

title: chicken barbecued
directions: Place chicken into a baking dish.
Mix dry onion soup mix, catsup and Pepsi.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° until chicken is tender.

title: summer waldorf rice salad
directions: Cook rice in water with salt according to package directions. When cooking is complete, transfer to shallow pan.
Cover and chill.
Fold whipped topping and sugar into mayonnaise.
Fold topping mixture, celery, apples, raisins and walnuts into chilled rice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon before serving.

title: mother's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender.
While hot, peel, cube and toss potatoes lightly with vinegar, margarine, sugar and salt. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, then add celery, eggs, parsley, pimiento, onion and pickle relish.
Chill until flavors blend.
Moisten with chilled Mayonnaise-Horseradish Sauce 1 hour before serving.

title: patty cake
directions: Put in greased Pyrex dish.
Mix and mash on bottom.

title: cinnamon popovers
directions: In blender container, combine eggs, milk, flour, butter or margarine, cinnamon and salt.
Cover and blend 30 seconds or until ingredients are combined.
Fill 6 to 8 well-greased custard cups or 2 1/2-inch muffin pans half full.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Prick tops with fork.
Remove from custard cups.
Serve hot with butter or margarine, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Mix one package of pressed ham with all the ingredients. Use remaining package of prssed ham on outside of roll.

title: cherry crunch or cherry cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, shortening, egg and baking powder to make batter.
Sprinkle about 1/2 cup sugar into skillet.
Pour cherries over sugar.
Add batter and bake in oven.

title: no yeast stir and roll pizza crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together; knead dough 10 times.
Roll out on floured board.
Brush with 1 tablespoon salad oil.
Top with your favorite toppings and bake in 450° oven.
Makes a 14-inch crust.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy. Slowly add sugar and beat well. Add oil, vanilla and zucchini; mix. Sift and add dry ingredients to mixture. Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour into 3 medium greased and floured loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: ellie mcdonald marinade
directions: Mix well together.
Take flank steak; pierce with fork and marinate overnight.
Barbecue or broil.
Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: potato soup
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Cover with water. Cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Fry bacon and drain.
Make white sauce of cornstarch and milk.
Add sauce to soup.
Add crumbled bacon; heat thoroughly.
Serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter; stir in flour.
Add water and stir until thickened.
Add cheese; stir well.
Remove from heat.
Add broccoli and beaten eggs.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole pan. Bake in a 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes.
Before baking, sprinkle bread crumbs over top with a dot of butter.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Set aside.
Roast the spareribs in a 500° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°.
Roast 1 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes with the sauce.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix & refrigerate cabbage and green onions. do not toast together as they require different cooking times. Mix
dressing in Jar. I store cabbage in fridge. Put noodles, sesame seeds, and almonds together.
Mix cabbage noodle mixture and dressing together just before serving. This keeps noodles from getting soggy.

title: everlasting slaw
directions: Bring to a rolling boil vinegar and sugar.
Cool slightly. Pour over rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator. This will keep a long time.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place each chicken wing in mixture, then place on a throw away cookie sheet.
Allow to marinate overnight.
Cook at 350° until each side is done, approximately 20 minutes on each side.

title: mexican stack-up
directions: Brown beef and onions. Drain. Add all ingredients except beans. Simmer for awhile, then add beans. Stack with the chips, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, olives and picante.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, lemon juice, mayonnaise, sugar and salt until smooth.
Drain fruit cocktail.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Freeze for 1 to 2 hours.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo
in casserole dish.
Mix cornbread mix, sour cream and corn in a
large mixing bowl.
Pour into casserole dish and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°, or until golden brown.

title: chilies rellenos with marinara sauce
directions: Divide Jack cheese evenly among chilies, folding or tucking cheese inside.
Arrange chilies side by side in bottom of greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
With electric mixer, mix eggs until thick and foamy; add milk and baking powder.
Beat until smooth as possible.
Pour egg batter over chilies, moistening evenly over all chilies.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Garnish with black olives.
Just before serving, top with heated marinara sauce or set sauce aside at table to be added when eaten.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; season.
Pour into pie shell (don't overfill).
Carefully take the other pie crust and gently place on top.
Smooth out and press edges together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Drain beets, keeping juice.
In saucepan, put juice and all ingredients except beets, onions and eggs.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Place beets, boiled eggs and onions in container.
Pour juice mixture over and seal.
Chill and let set overnight.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Place meatballs in a crock-pot. Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and pour over meatballs. Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion together until browned; add taco seasoning.
Layer all ingredients evenly in casserole pan.
Cook at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cut; serve warm.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on large flat plate.
Spread chili sauce over cheese.
Rinse crabmeat and sprinkle over chili sauce.
Serve with crackers for spreading.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle 2 cups crushed corn flakes on top.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel candies
directions: Place pretzels on waxed cookie sheet. Melt 1 or 2 bark squares in microwave 30 seconds to 1 minute. Pour into circle of pretzel. Top with M&M. Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: fruitcake cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Soak dates, cherries and pineapple in whiskey until all is absorbed. Add pecans, sugar, flour and eggs to fruit. Mix and spoon into cupcake tins. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: cream of garlic soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in melted butter for approximately 15 minutes.
Add chicken stock.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Strain off onion and garlic.
Add bread to strained broth.
Simmer 10 minutes. Remove and place broth and bread mix in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Return to stove.
Add cream and thyme.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cherry-cheese turnovers
directions: Blend cheese with butter, flour and salt; roll out dough.
Cut into 2 inch squares.
Place 1 tablespoon cherries in center of each square; fold over corners to seal.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: fried eggplant balls
directions: Cook the eggplant in boiling water until tender; peel it and mash up the pulp. Add remaining ingredients to the pulp and mix well. You may want to add a bit more crumbs if the mixture seems too thin for forming into balls. Shape into small balls and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Roll balls in flour and deep-fry until crisp. Serve hot.

title: pink pineapple punch
directions: Stir together.
Add 2-quarts ginger ale just before serving. Makes 4 quarts.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Mix together all but lemon-lime soda. Sugar to taste.
Water as needed to dilute. Chill at least 1 hour.
Add soda when ready to serve.
Can freeze some of mixture in ice cube trays, to be added to punch when served.

title: puff cutout cookies
directions: Cut flour, butter and Crisco as for pie crust.
In blender, combine cottage cheese and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Mix together as for pie crust.
Chill overnight.
Roll out and cut. Bake at 375° for 12 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease and flour square baking pan (or spray with Pam). Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece in mixture of sugar and cinnamon; coating well.
Place in random fashion in pan.
Sprinkle pecans over biscuits.
Melt margarine and brown sugar over low heat.
Cook until bubbly.
Pour slowly over biscuits.
Bake in preheated oven about 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: hunter's baked squirrel
directions: Dredge squirrels in seasoned flour and brown in enough oil in roasting pan.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Reduce temperature slowly for 45 minutes or longer until tender.

title: veggie pizza bites
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Unroll pizza crust dough; press dough on bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Stir together the butter, cocoa, sugar and eggs until blended. Add dry ingredients and vanilla; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 11 x 18-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with 1 package miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven long enough to melt but not brown the marshmallows.
Remove; cover with frosting while warm.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Scramble eggs until solid.
Fry the sausage.
Take shells and put cheese on bottom.
Spread with sausage and eggs.
Roll up. Spread on salsa (any amount you want).
Put in microwave and heat on High for 2 minutes.

title: harvest potatoes with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In small bowl, combine seasonings. Place 2 tablespoons of melted butter in a 10-inch nonstick skillet.

(If handle is not ovenproof, wrap with foil.) Arrange a third of the potato slices in a circular pattern in skillet. Sprinkle with about 1/4 teaspoon of seasoning, 4 teaspoons melted butter and 2 tablespoons of onion.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover tightly with foil; press layers down.
Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven. Press layers down with a spatula.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter to unmold potatoes.
Remove from skillet and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef tips over noodles
directions: Place large pot of water on to boil for the noodles and prepare noodles per instructions. While waiting for the water to come to a boil, melt the butter in a large pan. Saute the onion for a couple of minutes. Place beef in the skillet and brown on all sides (see note above). The fondue beef cooks quickly and takes about 5 to 10 minutes to cook. Add the can of mushroom soup and mix with the natural juices from the beef. Add the can of mushrooms and heat through. Drain the noodles and return to pot. Pour beef mixture over and toss.

title: coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and peppers until small.
Toss with sugar and salt.
Boil vinegar, oil, celery seed and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cool until lukewarm.
Pour over cabbage.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to one week.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 13 x 9-inch pan, forming a crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Dissolve Jell-O and water and add berries.
Set aside in fridge until chilled, just starting to gel.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Spread cream cheese mixture over crust, then pour Jell-O mixture over cream cheese layer and refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon poppy seed cake ring
directions: In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat sugar, margarine or butter, lemon extract, vanilla extract and eggs until blended. Increase speed to high and beat 5 minutes or until very thick, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour, milk, poppy seed, grated lemon peel, baking powder and salt.
Beat until well blended, scraping bowl often.
Grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer the onions, celery, pimentos, mushrooms and bell pepper in chicken broth until tender, then add chicken.
Make medium white sauce with milk, butter, soup and cheese.
Add spaghetti last and cook until done.
Salt and pepper.
English peas may be added.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.
Mix with popcorn; cook 1 hour in a 250° oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: walnut sour cream jumbles
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Cream butter with sugar, egg, vanilla and mace. Blend in flour mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in walnuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets, allowing room for spreading. Bake above oven center at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned very lightly. Remove to wire racks to cool. Makes about 25 to 35 cookies.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix crumbs and melted oleo; spread half in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Keep remaining crumbs for top.
Mix Dream Whip and milk until stiff.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix all together well.
Spread half of Dream Whip on top of crumbs in pan.
Gently spoon 2 cans of pie filling on top of Dream Whip.
Spread evenly with a knife.
Drop large spoonfuls of remaining Dream Whip on top of pie filling and spread with a knife.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on Dream Whip mixture.
Cover with Saran wrap and refrigerator for 24 hours.
(You can also make this ahead and freeze it.)

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread and let cool.
Crumble.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill before serving.
This keeps well in refrigerator.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 8-inch square pan.
Add wet ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Double recipe would make a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: nut spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and spices, add to butter mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch pieces.
Mix with all except cheese and onion rings.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: marinated cabbage salad
directions: Cut the cabbage head in chunks.
Use as many as desired of vegetables.
Mix all together.
Then pour bottle of Zesty Italian dressing over cabbage and vegetables.
Marinate overnight. Sprinkle bacon bits, if desired.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in a little salty water; drain and mash.
Cook hamburger and onion until done.
Mash meat to keep it from lumping, them drain and add pepper.
Crumble rice in eggplant, then add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Pour in dish and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: racioppi's braciole
directions: Rub mixture of butter and oil into one side of each piece of meat.
Rub salt and pepper into same side.
Spread layer of chopped garlic over same side.
Cover garlic with layer of bread crumbs.
Cover bread crumbs with layer of parsley.
Cover parsley with layer of chopped eggs.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in a blender or on high for 1 minute in a mixer.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 8 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, topped with grated cheese.
Put green lettuce around edge and tomatoes.

title: baked pie shell
directions: Mix shortening with flour and salt until pea size.
Put in water, working as little as possible.
Make into ball and chill. Roll out and put in pie pan and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and immediately add the Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Do not wait to cool.
Beat at once until thoroughly blended.
Pour in buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove skin and bones.
Combine all ingredients (except nuts).
Mix well.
Roll in nuts.
Chill for several hours.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Use mixer and cream together shortening and sugar.
Sift and then measure flour.
Add alternately flour and eggs, one at a time. Add lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in greased and floured angel cake pan at 312°.
Let cool slightly in pan and then turn out on cake rack.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain, place on paper towel.
Reserve drippings in small saucepan.
Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch. Add beaten egg with vinegar and mix well.
Add water, heat until thick.
Add crumbled bacon and drippings.
Serve warm over garden, spinach or endive salad.

title: rio lace cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, baking powder and sugar.
Blend eggs and oleo.
Mix with oatmeal mixture.
Add flavoring and pecans. Cover cookie sheets with foil.
Drop level teaspoonfuls of batter 2 to 3-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes, until lightly brown.
Cool before removing from foil.
(Foil can be reused a second time.)

title: a good snack
directions: Lay the crackers on a pan, then put 1/2 cup of nuts on top. Cook the butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
After the sauce comes to a boil, put the sauce on top of the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: green beans with tomatoes
directions: Saute onions in oil; add beans, tomatoes, salt and sugar. Cook about 1 hour.
If too juicy, add 2 tablespoons tapioca or cornstarch to thicken.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dry fish.
Dip in batter.
Fry fish in hot oil.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven.
Punch holes in top of cake with ice pick.
Have the Eagle Brand milk and orange juice or coconut milk mixed together and slowly pour milk mixture over cake.

title: cheesies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add a small amount of flour if not very stiff.
Form into 2 logs.
Roll in wax paper and leave in refrigerator for several hours.
Slice thin and bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not allow to get very brown.
Let cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour to thicken.
Add cream cheese to soften. Layer in casserole in this order: 1/2 wild rice, chicken, mushrooms and repeat.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 or 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Let set in refrigerator.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: boiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice muffins in half and arrange on broiler pan.
put all ingredients, except crab meat, into bowl and mix well.
Fold crab meat into mixture.
Spread on English muffins.
Broil until they puff up and are bubbly and slightly brown.
Can cut into triangles to serve.

title: cheesy rice latkes
directions: Combine brown rice, carrots, egg yolks, flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.

title: strawberry pudding or pie
directions: Mix pudding, jello and milk. Pour into bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour. You can also pour into pie crust for pie.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix well together.
Put in casserole and put buttered crumbs on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cucumbers a la creme
directions: Place cucumbers into salted boiling water.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter and add cucumbers.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, until tender.
Before serving, add cream and parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening.
Mix yeast and buttermilk.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture.

title: slow cooked beef stew
directions: Cut carrots in half crosswise.
Place beef, carrots and potatoes in slow cooker.
In a bowl, whisk together the soup, water and seasoning packet.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or high for 4 hours.

title: caramel-spice-oatmeal cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and spices.
Add sugars, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Shape in two 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: connecticut supper
directions: Brown onions in fat.
Add meat and water, cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour beef into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place potato slices over meat.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cereal.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!

title: b.b.q. cups
directions: The amount of ingredients for this recipe depends on individual taste.

title: carla's soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil raisins
in water a few minutes.
Let cool.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix soda in raisin juice (be sure you have 1 cup
of
juice).
Add juice to shortening mixture. Add dry ingredients.
Last add raisins and vanilla.
Mix well. Chill 1 hour in refrigerator.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Reserve broth.
Remove chicken from bones.
Lightly toss the stuffing with melted margarine. Serve 1 cup of the stuffing.
Place the remainder in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken over stuffing.
Pour chicken soup over stuffing.
Add 2 cups broth.
Top with reserved stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients, except noodles.
Stir in 1 cup noodles; mix gently.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; top with rest of noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all together; put enough water in mixture to make it sticky.
Roll mixture into balls and put balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Could be reheated in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water and add to gelatin.
Set aside to cool.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with sweet pickles or olives.

title: company lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, adding onions and garlic. Add chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, basil and sugar to meat. Simmer uncovered until thickened from 15 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese, and cottage cheese.
Butter a 9 x 13 inch lasagna pan and layer noodles, beef, cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut apples.
Mix everything thoroughly before adding sour cream.
Mix cream lightly.

title: rosamarina macaroni
directions: Combine juice from fruit with sugar, eggs, flour and salt and bring to a boiling point and let cool.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in 1-inch slices.
Butter a shallow baking dish. Place slices in dish side-by-side.
Brush tops with melted butter. Sprinkle with crumbs, then pecans.
Pour in cream and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 325° until tender.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add lemonade, cold water, ginger ale and cranberry cherry juice.
Drain juice from cherries. Put juice in punch.
Make ice cubes with cherries.
Put ice cubes in before serving.
Be sure to drain well, cherry juice doesn't freeze.

title: barbara flemings apple pie
directions: Using pastry blender cut together 2 1/2 c. flour, shortening and salt.
In small bowl mix 2 Tbsp. vinegar with enough milk to make one cup.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and mix.
Add additional flour until crust is no longer sticky and can be rolled out easily.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Place in pie plate lined with bottom crust.
Sprinkle with flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Slit top crust. Bake 10 minutes at 450° then lower heat to 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.
Check that apples are soft with fork or knife.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Set aside to cool.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, white sugar, flour, shortening, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and eggs.
Beat 2 or 3 minutes; mix in oatmeal.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes).

title: tater topped casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In skillet, cook onion, celery and ground beef until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain. Stir in salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over meat mixture.
Top with frozen potatoes and bake about 40 minutes or until bubbly. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Crush the strawberries and place in punch bowl.
Reconstitute the grapefruit juice and pour over the berries.
Add ice.
Add ginger ale and serve.
Makes 25 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Saute sausage with onion and celery; brown, if possible.
Mix sugar and flour until blended; add vinegar and water and stir until smooth.
Add to sausage and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour over potatoes and sliced eggs and blend together.
Serve hot.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Combine and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: wendy's beef burgundy
directions: Brown meat in olive oil (use 5-quart Dutch oven).
Add onions and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, bay leaf, thyme, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Add wine and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
In bowl, blend flour and butter.
Stir into stew mixture.
Heat to boiling, then simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until thickened.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mom's meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs and onion. Shape into balls. Brown in small amount of oil.
Put balls in oblong baking dish.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix eggs, butter, sugar, cocoa, flour, vanilla and pecans and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut marshmallows in half and put on top of hot cake while cake is still in pan.

title: mom's chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add juice, beans and chili seasoning. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat; add salt, garlic, soy sauce and water.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add more water as needed.
Put vegetables in and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch, blended in 1/4 cup water.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: quick fruit cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan, layer ingredients in order listed.
Do not stir ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1/2 cup butter and 1 egg with fork; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cheese with 1 pound powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread over first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients exactly 10 minutes at rolling boil.
Stir constantly!
Add remaining ingredients while stirring. Pour into sheet cake pan.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with filling. Refill whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.
When taking to a dance or picnic, place in cupcake papers to prevent tipping.

title: vivian green's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Retain 1/3 can tomato sauce.
Bake in metal pan 1 hour at 425°.
After cooking drain grease and top with sauce.
Cook 10-15 minutes more.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Add Jell-O and red hots to boiling water.
Heat until candies are melted.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour into greased Jell-O mold. Chill until firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Reserve all liquid.
Cook the pudding with the reserved liquid.
Cool completely.
Pour over fruit; mix together and serve.
If making ahead, wait until serving to put in the bananas.

title: beefy tostada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain excess grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Save 1 package of cheese for topping.
Top with rest of cheese.
Put in oven and bake until the cheese is good and browned, about 15 minutes.

title: squash bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and milk; stir lightly and set aside.
Combine squash, eggs and margarine; mix well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Heat 10-inch cast-iron skillet in 400° oven for five minutes. Combine all ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Remove skillet from oven and coat with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: pound cakes
directions: Mix well the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk, adding flour last.
Beat on high for 3 minutes after adding vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not open oven during cooking.

title: no bake oatmeal chocolates
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in heavy pot.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: honey of a punch
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Place allspice and cinnamon sticks in center of 6-inch square of cheesecloth and tie with string.
Add spices to punch mixture and simmer over medium-low heat for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Makes 17 (6-ounce) servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add the eggs and beat.
Add the vanilla, sour milk and dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in the grated zucchini.
You can sprinkle 1/2 cup chocolate chips and nuts on top of batter before baking, if you desire.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Take out 1 cup of the cake mix and put in bowl (set aside the one cup).
Blend with melted butter or oleo and egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (not greased).
Set aside.

title: fruit soup
directions: Cook tapioca with sugar, salt and 1 cup water until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 more cup water, frozen orange juice and strawberries.
Stir.
Add remaining drained fruit. Serve over sherbet.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and stir until dissolved, then add Crisco.
Mix good with a spoon.
Add box cake mix gradually, about half at the time.
Then, with a mixer, add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon flavoring, then pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: aunt jennie's corn pone
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In mixing bowl, beat together sugar and Crisco until blended; add eggs and salt.
Beat until blended; add buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix slightly on low speed; add cornmeal and flour.
Mix on low speed until dry ingredients are moist.
Beat on high speed with hand mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: chicken with artichoke hearts
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add mushrooms and saute until tender.
Remove and reserve.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Add to skillet and brown on both sides.
Add artichoke hearts, sherry and water (or chicken broth).
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add mushrooms last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Transfer all but liquid to serving platter. Keep warm.

title: oatmeal-spice cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in small bowl.
Beat butter and sugars in large bowl on high speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended. Stir in flour mixture, then oats and nuts.

title: quick bubble nut bread
directions: Put nuts in bottom of Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Separate biscuits and cut into quarters.
Roll biscuits in sugar and cinnamon.
Stack in pan.
Mix brown sugar and melted butter. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Remove from pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans; mix all ingredients into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 2 cups cracker crumbs mixed with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: helen's delight
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
In saucepan mix butter, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil, pour mix over flour and sugar.
Add soda, buttermilk, cinnamon, vanilla, eggs and salt.
Pour over greased baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Pan size is 18 x 12 x 1-inch.

title: joan's broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and pour over vegetables.
Stir and refrigerate several hours.

title: golden crunch coffee cake
directions: Sift together 3 cups flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream together 1/2 cup butter and eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Spread 1/2 batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over batter.
Spread with remaining batter; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (glass dish 35 to 40 minutes) or until golden.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peach melba cobblers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine peaches, raspberries and syrup, 1 tablespoon flour and cardamom or nutmeg. Blend well with a rubber spatula.
Evenly divide mixture among four 1-cup individual baking dishes.

title: sweet potato souffle crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased baking dish.
Cover with crunch topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Alternately add the flour and milk.
Add vanilla flavoring and coloring.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Ice with cream cheese icing after cake cools.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into small bite-size pieces.
Add diced onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together; pour over broccoli.
If to thick to pour easily, add a small amount of vinegar.
One half hour before serving, add bacon and mix well.

title: orange and raisin bread pudding
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer until combined. Add sugar, a little at a time; beat mixture until it ribbons when beater is lifted (8 to 10 minutes).
Add next 7 ingredients; beat until combined.
Line buttered 8-inch square baking dish with four slices of bread.
Top bread with half the orange pieces and half the raisins.
Spoon 1/3 of the custard over mixture.
Add another layer of bread; top with remaining pieces and raisins.
Spoon half of remaining custard over mixture.
Top with remaining bread slices; spoon rest of custard over bread, carefully pressing down on top layer so that it is covered with custard.
Cover pudding with plastic wrap.
Chill 1 to 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon basil chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts on top of onion and garlic in a shallow baking pan (well sprayed with cooking spray).
Combine lemon juice and olive oil and spoon on top.
Sprinkle basil leaves on top. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven until chicken is cooked through, about 20 minutes, depending on thickness.

title: sandies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes through cake with fork. Combine milk, sugar and coconut flavoring.
Heat to dissolve sugar mixture and then spoon on warm cake, allowing liquid to soak through holes.
Cool completely and then spread 8 ounce carton of Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Chill.

title: cherry and pineapple salad
directions: Combine all together in a bowl.
Chill until set firm.

title: baklava
directions: Mix nuts and sugar in bowl; set aside.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put sheet of phyllo in pan, extending up sides.
Brush with melted oleo.
Repeat 5 times.
Sprinkle with nut mixture.
Cut remaining leaves to fit 13 x 9-inch pan and repeat the layering 6 times; sprinkle with nuts.
Repeat this process 3 times.
Put remaining leaves, layered on last nut layer.

title: absent lady rice
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes.
Put fat in skillet; keep turning potatoes.
When almost done, add 3 to 4 teaspoons brown sugar and 3/4 cup sweet milk.
Place on low heat; let simmer until done.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown meat and 1/4 cup onion in skillet.
Stir in catsup, chili powder and salt.
Mash beans with liquid; heat.
Serve in chafing dish with shredded cheese sprinkled over top.
Serve with chips.

title: lace cookies(makes 36 cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to bubble.
Drop by level teaspoons into ungreased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes.
While still warm, remove from muffin tins.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in sugar while hot.
Let stand until mixture cools.
Whip Carnation milk until it stands in a peak, then stir in jello and sugar.
Add juice of 2 lemons and mix well.
Pour into a pan (9 x 11-inch) lined with crushed vanilla wafer crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top; refrigerate.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Poke holes through chicken and pour Italian dressing over chicken.
Let chicken set overnight for best results.
You may add moderate seasonings of your choice, but be mindful of your salt (Italian dressing contains a lot of salt).
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cover chicken and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Uncover chicken and bake until golden brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place in oven that has been preheated to 425°.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Spread dry rice in a large Pyrex dish.
Spread onion soup over rice.
Add water.
Arrange chicken breasts on top.
Spoon chicken soup over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Combine soup, cream, sherry and mushrooms in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Add parsley.

title: broccoli corn bread(quick and delicious)
directions: Spray a baking pan or iron skillet with vegetable spray.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: hard rock cafe chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add vegetables (onions, celery, green pepper, pimentos and garlic that have been chopped in food processor) to meat and saute a few minutes.
In large kettle, add tomatoes, browned meat mixture, all spices and beans.
Bring to a boil and simmer 4 to 6 hours on stove top at very low heat or place in oven and simmer at 325° same amount of time.

title: camptown brownies
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually while continuing to beat.
Melt butter, unsweetened chocolate and semi-sweet bits together in microwave and add with vanilla to egg mixture.
Fold in flour. Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Bake in greased 9-inch square pan at 350° about 30 minutes. The batter is thick. Cool before cutting into squares.

title: southern cobbler
directions: Put butter in baking dish and set in oven to melt.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon fruit on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch deep cake pan, dump in both cans of pie filling and pineapple with juice.
Mix well in pan and even out. Put box of dry cake mix on top and even it out.
Take frozen butter and slice very thin and lay all over top of cake.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and mix with water and taco seasoning as directed on the package.
Add salsa to keep meat moist.
Cook according to package.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook all together until falling apart, about 3 hours.
Remove bone and fat.
Serves 18 to 20 people.
(Traditional Christmas Eve supper in Dan's family for 3 generations plus.)
Place on buns and enjoy!

title: gooey chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still warm, poke holes with large tined fork. Spread can of condensed milk over top.
Cool slightly.
Spread ice cream topping over cake.
Spread whipped topping over top and sprinkle with crushed toffee candy.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: confetti spread
directions: Grind Spam in meat grinder or processor; add grated carrots, onion, green pepper and chipped eggs.
Add sugar, vinegar and Miracle Whip.
Mix well.
Very good sandwich spread.

title: mock souffle
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer bread, ham, Swiss and Cheddar, starting with a layer of bread.
Combine eggs, milk, onion powder and dry mustard; pour over layers.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover; sprinkle with corn flakes. Drizzle with butter or margarine.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: virginia's homemade ice cream(poor peoples' dessert)
directions: Mix all together and crank your heart out!

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn; place in roasting pan in oven at 200°.

title: corn meal mix
directions: Combine in a very large bowl and mix well. Place in an airtight container and use for the following recipes:
Corn Meal Muffins, Corn Meal Pancakes, Corn Meal Waffles and Whole Corn Pancakes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Mix well; do not overbeat.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in tube pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together brown sugar, peanut butter and vegetable oil.
Beat in egg.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in oven.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: yogurt fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Put in blender and blend about 1 minute.
Combine cold water and add ice cubes to make 1 cup.
Add to jello and stir until ice is almost melted.
Blend in yogurt.
Chill and serve.
Fresh fruit may be added if desired. Serves 5.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Place in jar and add marinade to cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, pineapple juice, lemon juice and salt. Cook over slow heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
When cool, add celery, apples, pineapple, walnuts and whipping cream. Freeze in pan.

title: bayou jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and rice in shortening until onion is transparent.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; simmer, stirring occasionally with fork, until rice is tender, about 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Over medium heat, cook corn meal and water, stirring until the batter becomes stiff and begins to roll into a ball (about 6 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in the milk, oil and onion. Gradually stir batter into eggs in a large bowl.
Stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together and blend into corn meal batter.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, about 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 30 to 40 hush puppies.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Place half the batter in a greased baking pan.
Add meat mixture.
Add the rest of the batter.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together lemonade, yogurt and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill well.

title: banana oatmeal cake
directions: Combine mashed bananas, oatmeal and lemon juice.
Let set. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients. Combine and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Mix ingredients, drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes between 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Mix chili sauce, water, bread crumbs, spices and egg. Add venison and knead 3 to 5 minutes. Shape and place in greased pan. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken, rice and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Heat margarine in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.
Add onion and celery; cook and stir until tender.
Stir in water, soup, vegetables, paprika, poultry seasoning and thyme. Cover; bring to a boil.
Stir in chicken and rice.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with biscuits. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Shred lettuce and cheese.
Cut onion and tomatoes.
Crush chips slightly.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 7 x 8-inch pan.
Pour dough over peaches.
Bake at 315° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican bean casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup of corn chips and 1/2 cup grated cheese. Combine remaining ingredients, chips and cheese with sauces and onion and put into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Spread top with remaining sour cream and sprinkle remaining crushed chips in a circle form.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add 3 whole eggs plus 1 yolk, one at the time; mix well.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and add alternately with the flour, beating well.
Fold in pecans.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix well; pour into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.

title: sue's fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients, except 1 tablespoon margarine for 3 minutes.
Add chopped nuts.
Take the tablespoon of margarine and coat pan with it, then pour fudge and let set.

title: janet's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk, gradually stirring in eggs.
Add next 3 ingredients and a dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle butter crumbs over the top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream light brown and white sugars with softened butter.
Add Karo, baking soda, peanut butter and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips and M&M's.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown on top.

title: creole mac(serves 6)
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Saute green pepper and onion in oleo until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir over medium heat until thoroughly heated.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown together the hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add the chili beans, baby limas and pork and beans.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white lasagna
directions: In saucepan, heat cubes of butter until melted.
Add flour and mix with wooden spoon.
Mix until pale gold in color.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Put back on heat to thicken.
Add Cheddar or Muenster cheese to taste, starting with 1/2 cup.
Add 2 eggs to Ricotta cheese and blend well.
In baking dish, alternate Cheddar cheese sauce, noodles, and Ricotta mixture, top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fudge marshmallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips with peanut butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth. Fold in marshmallows. Pour into greased 9-inch pan; chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Warm cottage cheese, then add sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, yeast and egg.
Stir.
Add flour gradually and mix thoroughly.
There is no kneading necessary.
Let rise 1 hour and punch down.
Shape into 1 loaf and place in well-greased bread pan.
Let rise until double in bulk. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Brush with melted butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add garlic powder and saute onion and mushrooms.
Cook broccoli according to package directions or until tender (if fresh).
Cook rice.
Drain margarine from onion and mushrooms.
Microwave Cheez Whiz until soft enough to pour.
Mix all ingredients together in large casserole dish.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: chops and greens
directions: Place turnip greens in a large pot; sprinkle sugar on greens. Lay turnip slices on top of greens.
Lay pork chops on greens and turnips.
Pour grease from fried white bacon over greens, chops and turnips.
Add water to pot; cook on high until water starts to boil.
Reduce to low heat; cook, covered, about 45 yo 60 minutes, until greens are done.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple.
Combine reserved juice, barbecue sauce and honey.
Pour over chicken and bake an additional 25 minutes, basting occasionally.
Arrange pineapple over chicken; bake 10 minutes longer.
(Fat can be drained off chicken before adding sauce.)
Serve chicken over steamed rice.

title: soft crust chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Add salt and pepper.
Mash and dissolve chicken bouillon cube. Add soup and broth. Heat to boiling.
Grease casserole.
Place chicken on bottom. Sprinkle with the eggs.
Pour broth over chicken.
Mix flour, butter and milk until smooth.
Spoon all over chicken to cover.
Bake at 350° until done and top is browned.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery

title: diet sandwiches
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix cottage cheese, salmon and horseradish. Pack on bread.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Sprinkle chicken with cornstarch; toss to coat well.
Add sherry and soy sauce; marinate 15 minutes at room temperature. Heat oil in uncovered wok to medium-high (375°).
Add chicken; stir-fry for 4 minutes.
Add mushrooms and green peppers; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to mix.
Serve immediately over fluffy white rice.
Serves 4.

title: good chocolate cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Mix cocoa, soda, salt and baking powder; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into two 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and ice with your favorite icing.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all the above ingredients.
Melt 1 stick margarine. Crush 1 stack Ritz crackers and mix with margarine and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, and egg yolks, and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients, sift 3 times, and add to sugar, oil & egg mixture. Add buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring, beating with mixer until mixed well. Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Pour in 4 to 5 well-greased layer cake pans.
Bake 320 degrees preheated oven. Cool and ice with cream cheese icing (recipe follows).

title: pesto cream cheese dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and pesto sauce and parmesan Cheese in a bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: bean and corn dip
directions: Mix salsa, beans, corn, olives, tomato and cheese together. Chill.
Serve with chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Then add pineapple, then add cake mix and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs until foamy and stir in milk and oil.
Add flour and salt and beat until smooth (about 1 minute).
Fill hot greased popover pan (or muffin tin) 1/3 full and bake at 450° for about 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer, until popovers are firm.
Makes about 8.

title: cheesy onion casserole
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Simmer onions and oil in a covered pan for 20 minutes.
Crumble the bread and mix in with the grated cheese; set aside 1 cup of this mixture to put on top of casserole.
Heat soup and milk.
Combine all of this in a casserole dish and put remaining cheese and bread crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy shortcake]
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until browned, at 425°.
Serve warm, topped with fresh strawberries.

title: jaegerschnitzel(german pork fillets)
directions: Salt and pepper the fillets, then turn in flour until well coated.
Cook slowly in butter along with onions and mushrooms. When done (about 15 minutes each side), remove from pan and keep warm.
Pour 1 cup warm water into pan to loosen the juices.
Add bouillon and more flour if you want a thicker gravy.
Simmer for 1 minute.
Place fillets on a serving platter and cover with gravy. Serve with noodles and salad.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Separate each roll into three parts and place on cookie sheet.
Spoon on crab meat mixture.
Top with slice of water chestnut.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, sugar and one package of coconut together.
Store in a covered container and refrigerate overnight.
Punch holes in cake with a fork.
Spread sour cream mixture over cake.
(Most of mixture will soak into cake.)
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle other package of coconut over Cool Whip.

title: the one and only best carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Add carrots and oil and mix well by hand.
Add eggs and beat by hand until well mixed.
Blend in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not frost.
(If your oven tends to run hot, bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.)

title: creamy italian pasta salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredientsand stir in remainder. Cover and chill. Serves 3.

title: people chow
directions: Combine all chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until melted, stirring occasionally, to blend well.*
Pour over cereal in a large bowl. Stir gently to coat well.
Combine with confectioners sugar in a large plastic bag. Shake until cereal is evenly coated.
Store in covered container at room temperature.
Serves 25.

title: easy roast beef
directions: Sprinkle dry onion soup mix, salt, and pepper over meat. Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: microwave fruit pudding
directions: Spread pie filling in 8-inch square microwave-safe dish.
In small bowl, mix 1/2 box yellow cake mix, melted butter, nuts and cinnamon.
Spread evenly over pie filling.
Microwave on High for 11 to 13 minutes; turn 1/4 turn half way through.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: layered italian beef pie(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie crust 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Brown ground beef. Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Beat eggs in bowl and add Parmesan and spinach.
Put 1/2 of meat into crust. Sprinkle with 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Spoon spinach evenly over cheese. Top with rest of meat.

title: no-fat mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients on serving platter in order given.
Serve with Frito-Lay baked Tostitos tortilla chips.

title: linguini with lemon
directions: In a large saucepan, cook linguini in boiling salt water. While pasta cooks, melt butter in large skillet.
Add cream and vodka; simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Layer:
bread, cheese and sausage in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat eggs with 2 cups milk.
Pour over layers.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Mix soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over top of chilled mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen strawberry squares
directions: Note:
If you use frozen strawberries, be sure to decrease sugar to just 2/3 cup.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with electric mixer. Pour into loaf pans or Bundt pans, oiled.
