Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaf pans.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Cook pie crust in oven; cool.
Mix dry ingredients of pie filling mixture in club aluminum saucepan (stainless steel will burn easier).
Add butter, milk and beaten egg yolks.
Reserve egg whites for meringue.
Important:
Do not add crushed pineapple until mixture has cooked awhile and thickened.
Pineapple will curdle milk if added too soon.
Take pan off heat.
Add pineapple and stir well.
Pour into pie crust.
Heap your favorite meringue recipe onto hot filling and seal edges to prevent shrinking.
Bake and cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 3 quart pot, mix 4 cups sugar, 2 cups Karo syrup, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup water.
Mix and cook to 230°.
Add 4 1/2 cups raw peanuts.
Cook to 300°.
Add 1 tablespoon oleo and 2 teaspoons soda.
This will make it foam!
Remove from heat and pour onto well greased cookie sheets.
Work fast!
Makes 4 1/2 pounds.

title: homemade onion rings
directions: Clean onions and cut into 1/4-inch slices; separate into rings.
Combine beaten egg yolk and milk.
Add flour, salt and melted Crisco.
Mix until smooth.
Dip onion rings into batter. Fry in deep fryer until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towel. Serve hot.

title: cocktail nibbles
directions: Melt oleo.
Add
seasonings.
Cover
cereal
and
nuts. Mix together well.
Bake
at 225° for 1 hour, covered.	Remove cover; bake 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: cool chocolate chip dessert
directions: Dip cookies in milk and place in bottom of dish.
Smooth layer of Cool Whip over cookies. Repeat layers of cookies dipped in milk and layer of Cool Whip, ending with layer of Cool Whip.
Crumble cookies on top and chill for a minimum of 3 hours.

title: garden club veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Put crackers and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients, then cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Place apple slices in two 1-cup casserole dishes.
Sprinkle mixture with sugar and oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large, heavy pan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Allow to stand 12 hours. Strain and re-warm to serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash casserole
directions: In skillet, cook onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Mix squash, cornbread, cream of chicken soup, sage, onion and celery. Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: ham and cheese biscuits pleasers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate biscuits to make 10.
Pat or roll each to a 4-inch circle.
Wrap ham slice around the cheese cube.
Wrap biscuit circles around ham and cheese, pressing edges to seal.
Dip in melted butter and then cracker crumbs.
Place seam side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: layered casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Cook meat in large skillet until browned.
Drain fat.

Add salt, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic, and pepper; simmer over low heat 5 to 10 min. Combine noodles with sour cream, cream cheese, and green onion. Arrange meat mixture and noodle mixture in alternate layers in a 2 qt. casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 25 min.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli; cut into flowerets.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Layer salad, starting with broccoli, then bacon and onion.
Add dressing and then grated cheese to your taste.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mishelle's chili
directions: Brown onions.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Stir in beans, chili powder and sugars.
Simmer 1 hour while browning beef in separate pan.
Add beef and simmer 2 more hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at low speed on mixer for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in oblong pan.
Cool; serve with Cool Whip.

title: cheddar-almond spread
directions: Chop onions and almonds (fine); crumble bacon. Blend all ingredients together. Serve with crackers. Do ahead. Easy. Yield: 2 cups.

title: italian spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Cover; simmer (200° to 210°) for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Serve meat sauce over hot spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grapefruit jelly
directions: Measure sugar; set aside.
Measure grapefruit juice into large pan.
Stir in Sure-Jell and mix.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Add sugar; bring to a rolling boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour into jars.
Top with paraffin.

title: tanis' dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple, pie filling and dry cake mix into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all together.
Cut up butter into little chunks and sprinkle over the top.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour, apples and sour cream. Spoon into unbaked 9-inch crust.
Combine Rice Krispies or corn flakes, cinnamon, nutmeg, flour, brown sugar and softened butter. Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Cook over boiling water.
Stir continuously until thick. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in hot mixture and egg yolks.
Cook 2 minutes. Stir in coconut and vanilla. Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar. Beat until fluffy.

title: chicken pie
directions: Spread chicken in casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 stick melted butter over chicken.
Spread cream of chicken soup over.
Sprinkle English peas over.
Pour in 1 1/4 cups chicken broth.
Mix in eggs.
Mix 1 stick butter, flour, milk and pour on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cracker treats
directions: Place graham crackers evenly on a cookie sheet.
Bring oleo and brown sugar to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and pecans; stir.
Pour over crackers and spread to cover.
Bake at 325° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Break apart after cooled.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream together butter and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients. Make small balls of this mixture and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry fruited celery
directions: Slice celery diagonally about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick (or thicker if you like).
In a large skillet or wok, heat oil until very hot.
Add celery and onions; saute 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add apple, raisins, salt and ginger; saute 3 minutes or just until celery is tender-crisp.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Brown together the meat, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add the cottage cheese, sour cream, cream cheese and tomato sauce.
Simmer this mixture 1/2 hour.
Alternate layer of noodles and meat mixture in baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: healthy omelet
directions: Mix egg substitute and milk in bowl.
Set aside.
Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Place on burner and heat.
Pour mixture in hot skillet.
Scatter vegetables on one-half side of mixture.
Fold plain half side of mixture onto vegetables.
Flip omelet several times until light brown.
Enjoy without any guilt.

title: sage cheese ball
directions: Blend together.
Add lemon juice, sage and garlic.
Form into a ball.
Chill overnight.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sure-fire chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken and dice.
Halve grapes.
Chop celery and mix together.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Stir in just enough mayonnaise to moisten and blend.
Ingredients may be varied according to taste. Serves 6 to 8.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water; cool.
Beat butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Beat into chocolate mixture alternately with buttermilk. Beat the egg whites stiff; fold into batter.
Grease and flour 3 9-inch cake pans; line bottoms of pans with waxed paper.
Pour batter evenly into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans to finish cooling on racks.
Spread frosting between layers and over top.

title: mish mash
directions: Shape ground beef into individual oblong patties. Garlic salt and salt and pepper to taste.
Broil until desired doneness.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, chopped tomatoes and chopped green onion.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all other ingredients and microwave until cheese melts, about 2 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Use 9 x 13 pan.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Store in tightly sealed container.
Use 2 teaspoons to make a delicious cup of hot tea.

title: no guilt chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 9-inch pie plate, place mixture of soup, vegetables and chicken.

title: finger burritos
directions: Mix ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Allow to set in refrigerator at least 1 hour or overnight.
Cut into 1-inch pieces, discarding ends.

title: pralines
directions: Fill cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Boil 2 minutes 1 cup oleo and 1 cup brown sugar.
Pour over graham crackers and top with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Press 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with rhubarb.

title: famous creamy marshmallow fudge
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9-inch pan.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, milk, marshmallows and salt.
Heat over medium heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
When bubbles cover entire surface, continue to boil for 5 more minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat and beat in chocolate chips, nuts, margarine and vanilla.
Continue to beat until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread in buttered pan and chill until firm.

title: make ahead quick and easy chicken(makes 5 dinners for 4 people)
directions: Will also need 5 (1-qt.) freezer bags.

title: quick and easy squash casserole(microwavable)
directions: Drain squash into a large glass casserole dish.
Slice large pieces with a knife.
Add soup, onion, drained mushroom pieces, grated cheese, salt and pepper and most of the stuffing mix to the squash.
Stir and mix well.
Sprinkle the top of the casserole with a layer of stuffing mix.
Put 4 to 5 dabs of butter on top for extra flavor.
Microwave on High 9 minutes.
Turn the dish a quarter turn.
Microwave 9 additional minutes.

title: pesto
directions: Combine the basil, garlic and walnuts in the bowl of a food processor or half the recipe and use a blender to chop.
Leave motor running and add olive oil in a slow, steady stream.
Shut blender off, add cheeses, a big pinch of salt and a liberal grinding of pepper.
Process briefly to combine, then scrape into a bowl and cover until used.
Makes 2 cups, enough for 2 pounds of pasta.

title: refrigerator pies
directions: Drain pineapple well and mix with Cool Whip, sweet milk, lemon juice and nuts.
Pour into shells and chill until filling firms.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple good. Add Cool Whip and other ingredients. Pour in dish and chill.

title: mozzarella and artichoke dip
directions: Easy to make.
Drain and chop up artichokes.
Grate Mozzarella.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish. Microwave on High for 20 minutes; turn 90° halfway through (edges may brown) or 325° for 1 hour.

title: unstuffed cabbage casserole(quick one-dish meal)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: jello delight
directions: Mix
all
ingredients;	let
marshmallows begin to dissolve. Wait
until
jello	has
cooled slightly before adding bananas. Chill until firm in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt chips in the top of double boiler.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Stir well.
Drop onto wax paper by a teaspoon.
Let stand until set.

title: unfried potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Slice the potatoes into fries.
Coat the cookie sheet with 3 sprays of Pam.
Combine the beaten egg whites and spice mix in a bowl.
Add the potatoes and mix.
Place in a single layer on the bottom shelf of the oven.
Bake about 40 minutes, turning.

title: dressed bananas
directions: Grind enough peanuts to coat 6 bananas.
Cut bananas in halves and coat with salad dressing.
(Mayonnaise may be used.)
Roll bananas in peanuts to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: In a large bowl combined pudding (already mixed) and Cool Whip.
Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish, cover bottom of dish with whole graham crackers.
Pour on top of the graham crackers 1/2 of the pudding mixture.
Cover that with another layer of whole graham crackers, then pour rest of pudding mixture on top of graham crackers.
Crumble graham crackers on top of the pudding mixture. Keep chilled.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine in medium-sized saucepan the first 5 ingredients. Bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 3 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in oatmeal and extract.
Beat until thickened and cool.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Chill well.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil in a skillet.
Add onion, pepper and rice.
Cook lightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: liver pate spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and braunschweiger.
Mix thoroughly by hand or mixer.
Add all other ingredients and blend thoroughly. Place in serving dish and top with sliced olives or parsley flakes for added appeal.
Delicious with any type of cracker or crunchy bread chips.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers in kettle with sugar and vinegar. Bring to full rolling boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add pectin. Mix and let stand for 5 minutes, stir again. Fill jelly jars 1/4 inch from top; turn jars upside down for 5 minutes or more to set seals.

title: light orange jello
directions: Mix together crushed pineapple, juice and all, and orange Jell-O.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from burner when mixture begins to bubble and let cool.
When Jell-O is cooled, mix together buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Blend together with pineapple and Jell-O.
Pour in a 9 x 13 pan or glass dish.
Cool and serve.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 1/4 gallon of warm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add warm water, sugar, salt, dry milk and oil in mixer. Blend good.
Add yeast mix.
Then add flour and blend.
When dough starts to pull from sides, it's ready to roll and cut.
Let stand and rise then.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Mix and let set overnight. Wrap bacon around each chestnut. Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes. Serve right out of the oven.

title: cheesy bacon bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cream cheese, bacon, onion and pepper. Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles and pinch seams together. Spread cheese mixture onto each rectangle. Roll up, starting at longest side and seal. Cut each roll into 16 slices. Place slices cut side down on cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder.
Add 1 spoonful at a time alternately with milk and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple and juice.
Blend well.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when touched.
Run knife around edge.
Set on rack to cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Milk, margarine and shortening at room temperature.
Cream sugar, shortening and margarine until creamy.
Add one egg at a time, beating well.
Add 1/2 flour and 1/2 milk; beat well.
Add remainder of flour and milk.
Bake in a large tube pan, greased with shortening and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool about 15 minutes before turning onto plate.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine until medium soft.
Drain and rinse with cool water.
Mix 3/4 of the bottle of salad dressing and 3/4 of the bottle of Salad Supreme with the noodles in a large bowl. Marinate overnight with the lid on.
Next morning, add the vegetables and mix around.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar, Wesson oil and water together.
Bring to a boil, then set aside to cool.
Mix all the vegetables together, then pour the dressing over them.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over low heat.
When melted, stir in peanuts.
Drop onto waxed paper and let stand until firm.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store mix in an airtight jar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered 3-quart baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil or lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Make a well in center of pan and mix in next 3 ingredients.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and peanut butter.
Add unbeaten eggs. Beat well; add flour, soda and salt sifted together.
Form into balls and flatten with a fork dipped into sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts from bread and roll flat. Cream butter, cheese, egg yolks and sugar together. Spread on flattened bread and roll up. Spread with melted butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Combine in a 9 x 13-inch greased glass pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: upside banana split cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When done, pour pineapple juice over cake.
Mix pudding as directed.
When done, add cream cheese; stir until well blended.
After cake cools, slice bananas and put on cake, then add pineapple.
Add pudding mix.
Top with Dream Whip and decorate with nuts.

title: lentil roast
directions: Brown finely minced onion in part of oil.
Mash lentils and add all ingredients.
Bake in oiled loaf pan at 375° for about 1 hour. Serve with desired gravy.
Serves 12.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; parboil sliced potatoes. Layer ground beef, potatoes, onions and cheese. Top with layer of cheese and cream of mushroom soup. Bake at 350° until done.

title: "peach on the beach"
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour about 12 ounces into blender with ice cubes.
Blend and serve.
Repeat.

title: quesadillas
directions: Fry each tortilla in 1/4 inch of hot oil until crisp and golden, turning once; drain.
Place tortillas on paper towels. Sprinkle with combined cheeses; top with tomato.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut each tortilla into quarters; top with cilantro.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Alternately layer potatoes, bell pepper
and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and pepper to taste.
Pour over potato mixture; cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Put 2/3 cup of cream and all of butter in saucepan and simmer over medium heat until thickened.
Turn off heat.

title: hot fudge sundae sauce
directions: Stir together chocolate chips, margarine, sugar and Carnation and simmer.
Boil easy for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and cool.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To serve, place 2 well rounded teaspoonfuls into 1 cup boiling water.
Stir.
Add cinnamon stick. Makes excellent gift.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter bottom of cake pan.
Put all dry ingredients in a bowl. Crumble butter all together; put apples in pan.
After all ingredients are mixed in a bowl, put over apples and bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: beef stew(slow cooker)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Use to coat beef stew cubes. Heat shortening in skillet; add beef cubes and brown.
Transfer to slow cooker.
Add carrots (cut into pieces), sliced celery, large sliced onion, garlic clove, canned tomatoes and bay leaf.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate until firm.
Beat together the last 4 ingredients until smooth and top Jell-O layer.

title: krispie treats
directions: Melt the chocolate in a double boiler or in the microwave. Stir in the peanuts and cereal.
Drop in bite-sized clusters onto wax paper and allow to cool.

title: pixie cookies
directions: Stir margarine, baking chocolate and cocoa over low fire (don't let stick).
In mixing bowl, add to mixture the sugar, then eggs.
Beat well.
Add to chocolate mixture the flour, baking powder and salt.
Refrigerate overnight or 6 to 8 hours.
Roll tablespoon of chocolate mixture into a ball and roll in confectioners sugar until all white.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 18 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Add 1 unbeaten egg.
Mix well, then add the other egg. Add vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Add flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour in baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm. Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cut apples into bite-sized pieces. Dip sliced apples into the mixture.
At Christmastime use red and green apples.

title: cheese cake
directions: Open and roll out crescent rolls into the bottom of a foil lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, sugar, sour cream and cream cheese and pour over crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage-carrot salad
directions: Put all items into bowl and mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: seven vegetable salad
directions: Mix all in one pan and serve.

title: raisin juice cake
directions: Just cover raisins with water and cook until plumped.
Pour off and reserve 1/2 cup of juice.
Cream butter and sugar well. Add unbeaten egg.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with juice.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in shallow greased and floured pan at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: poultry dressing
directions: Cook celery, onion and poultry seasoning in butter until vegetables are tender.
Add soup and mix lightly with bread cubes. Makes about 4 cups.

title: green beans
directions: Drain green beans; rinse with cold water and drain again. Pour chicken broth into saucepan.
Add beans; cook for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Tastes like fresh cooked beans without the fat and salt.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until tender and falls off bone; add all ingredients together and simmer for 1 hour.

title: harriett's broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside.
Mix cornmeal mix, eggs, broccoli, onion and cottage cheese; mix well and pour into pan of melted butter.
Spoon melted margarine all over top of cornmeal mixture.
Bake for approximately 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Divide popcorn between 2 ungreased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Keep warm in a 200° oven while preparing caramel.
Heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges or until 248° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda until foamy and uniform in color.
Pour over corn, stirring until well coated. Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry, raspberry or pineapple squares
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, Grape-Nuts and margarine.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring often into crumbs.
Drain some of juice from fruit.
Combine egg whites, sugar and lemon juice with fruit in large mixing bowl and beat on high speed until soft peaks (maybe 10 minutes).
Fold in large Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with filling and then rest of crumbs.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Can be made several days in advance.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Sort through for bad beans.
Parboil 10 minutes until skins split if you blow on them.
Mix sugar and salt together; cut bacon into 1-inch squares.
Drain beans.
Layer in crock-pot; start with bacon and end with same.
Cook with enough water to cover for 8 to 10 hours, stirring every once in awhile. Cook covered.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch crisps
directions: Melt butterscotch chips over low heat.
Quickly add large can of Chinese noodles and medium package of cashews.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: cheesy french bread appetizers(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients, except French bread, until well blended.
Cut bread into 1/4-inch slices; spread on cheese mixture.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes, or until process cheese food is melted.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place confectioners sugar in a bowl.
Cut in the peanut butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Set aside 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs into the pie shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer the chicken, soup combined with 1 cup of chicken broth and 1 package stuffing mix combined with chicken broth to desired consistency.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Shape in ball all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Pull out, top with more cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Eat with crackers.

title: cheese cake for weight watchers
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth; mix in yogurt, lemon juice and pudding mix.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and top with fruit, if you desire.
Chill.
Easy and delicious.

title: baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook rice according to package directions. In a large oven proof dish, beat eggs, whisk in vanilla, salt, sugar and milk. Add cooked rice. To prevent rice from sticking to sides, place in a water bath with about 2 inches of water. Bake for 30 minutes, sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar and bake an additional 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: beef and vegetable stew
directions: Brown meat in oil. Add seasoning. Cover with water.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Add potatoes, vegetables and enough broth to cover.
When potatoes and vegetables are cooked, mix flour and water. Add to stew until desired thickness.
Simmer for at least 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix flour with margarine.
Add pecans.
Pat into 8 or 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 2-quart greased dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until well browned.

title: 1 dish meal
directions: Brown chicken breast (cubes).
Cook noodles; drain.
Drain peas, corn and carrots.
Add soups and other ingredients and a little milk.
Stir to mix.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Wash peppers and clean out insides well.
Fill with the above mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butternut squash
directions: Peel squash and scoop out seeds.
Cut into 2-inch chunks. Place in a heavy saucepan and add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until squash is soft.
Stir often.
Remove from heat and beat with an electric mixer to blend, like mashing mashed potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal-sunflower bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and salt; let stand 1 hour. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add yeast to oats after they have stood 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients in order. Knead in enough flour (any extra should be of whole wheat as there is enough white to allow this bread to be light) to make a smooth velvety dough.
Let rise to twice original size.
Knead down. Shape into 2 loaves, place in oiled bread pans and cover.
Let rise to 2/3 finished size (allowing for 1/3 rise in oven) and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
A delicious sandwich bread.
Try it with mayonnaise and alfalfa sprouts.

title: bombay celery sticks
directions: In a small bowl, mix cream cheese, peanuts and chutney until well blended.
Stuff each rib of celery with 1 tablespoon of cheese mixture.
Cover and chill.
Cut into 2-inch pieces.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, soup, carrots, onion and sour cream together and season with salt and pepper to taste. Melt margarine with 2 cups cornbread (crumbled fine). Leave 3/4 cup of cornbread mixture for top of casserole. Line the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish with remainder of cornbread mixture (about 1 1/4 cups). Add squash mixture. Sprinkle the 3/4 cup of cornbread mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet cashew milk
directions: Blend the 1 cup water and cashews; add the 3 cups water, dates and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Makes 1 quart.

title: noodle and ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Arrange noodles and ham in layers in a greased casserole, sprinkling each layer with grated onion. Combine soup and milk; pour over noodles.
Top with crumbs and a dash of paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until browned.
Makes about 6 servings.
I prefer cream of chicken soup.

title: monster cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix in dishpan in order given.
Drop by large spoon or ice cream scoop and flatten, about 6 to a cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake! Recipe does not call for flour.

title: mix ahead bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine first three ingredients.
Stir together at low until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix on low until moistened.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before baking.

title: garden fresh soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy kettle.
Saute onions and garlic until transparent; add zucchini and green pepper.

Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until lightly browned (around 10 minutes). Add the remaining ingredients, except macaroni; bring to boil. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are barely tender.
Add macaroni and simmer for 4 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: mushrooms neptune
directions: Preparation of Neptune Mix:
Place cream cheese in large mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Squeeze crab meat and shrimp in a towel to extract as much water as possible.
Roughly chop by hand the crab meat, shrimp meat and green onions so there is still some texture to ingredients.
Add chopped seafood, onions, Parmesan cheese, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, lemon juice and Tabasco to cream cheese.
Blend at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the chocolate over low heat. Stir in the peanuts.
Drop on wax paper by spoonful.
Let harden about 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate coconut bonbons
directions: Mix milk and butter with mixer at high speed.
Turn to low then cream in sugar, salt and vanilla; then back to high a minute. Remove mixer and mix by hand the nuts and coconut.
Let chill, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Make into balls the size of an English walnut.
Chill again in refrigerator at least an hour or more.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cube potatoes and boil.
Mash with electric mixer.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Set aside.

title: pat's fresh peach pie(a pretty summer dessert!)
directions: Slice 2 to 3 peaches onto the crust (one layer).
Mix other 3 ingredients until smooth (2 minutes, medium speed).
Pour into crust.
Slice remaining peaches and arrange on top in "sunburst" design.
Refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place crumbs in mixing bowl.
Mix milk, sugar and butter.
Add to crumbs and mix well. Slowly add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caroline's cheese cake
directions: Make graham cracker crust in a 9-inch spring-form pan, building crust up the sides 1/2 from top of pan.

title: italian marinated tomatoes
directions: Place oil and all ingredients, except tomatoes, in shaker and shake until well mixed. Pour dressing over tomatoes; toss gently to mix well. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Heat corn syrup, oleo and chocolate chips to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large mixing bowl; toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand until firm, at least 1 hour.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 48 squares.

title: easy three day sweet pickles
directions: Pour juice off of pickles and discard.
Fill jar with cold water and let stand for 2 hours.
Drain and discard water.
Cut pickles into 1/2-inch slices and return to gallon jar.
Cover with sugar, garlic, spices and vinegar; seal.
Let stand for 3 days, turning jar upside-down and right side up from time to time. Store in a cool place.

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine 1/3 cup of milk, 1/3 cup soup and eggs.
Mix well. Add stuffing mix and tuna.
Mix lightly.
Shape into 4 to 8 patties. Heat margarine in large skillet.
Brown patties.

title: lettuce au gratin
directions: Remove outside leaves from lettuce heads and save them for salad.
Cut the heads in half and place in a colander; pour a kettleful of boiling water over them, then drain thoroughly.
While they are draining, make up one recipe of Bechamel sauce.
(A mornay sauce may be used with this dish as well.)
In the bottom of a buttered baking dish, arrange 3 of the lettuce heads; top with half the sauce.
Mix Accent with the buttered crumbs, about 1/2 teaspoon of salt and a few grains of pepper.
Sprinkle 1/2 the crumbs over the sauce.
Top with remaining lettuce, sauce and finally, the rest of the crumbs.
Dot with butter; bake until brown in a moderate oven (350°).

title: black label sirloin roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast on rack in shallow baking pan.
Combine rest ingredients in saucepan; heat until sugar melts.
Baste roast with sauce and cook 2 1/2 hours.
Baste frequently during cooking.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat oleo and Crisco with electric mixer; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into three 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until sides loosen from pans.
Set on racks and cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Cut strip of bacon into small pieces to be arranged on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey ham stew(from share)
directions: In slow cooker or crock-pot, put potatoes, carrots, beans, peas, tomatoes and broth. Add meat and add cabbage last.
Cover and let simmer all day until very tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mama jo's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in 9 X 13 greased and floured pan. Coat 1 c. pecans in 1/4 c. flour and sprinkle over mixture. Bake 35 minutes in 350 degree oven. Melt butter over hot cake. No need for icing!

title: chicken croquettes
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and add flour to make a roux.
Remove from heat and whisk in milk.
Return to heat and bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Put 1 cup of white sauce in a large mixing bowl and add ground chicken, onion, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well and spread the mixture into a shallow pan to speed up the cooling process and chill thoroughly, about 30 minutes.
Lightly beat egg with water.
Shape meat mixture into croquettes, dip in egg wash, then bread crumbs and pan or deep fry until golden brown.
Drizzle remaining white sauce over cooked croquettes.
Makes 8 croquettes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Layer in a baking dish the peas, asparagus and chestnuts.
Mix together butter and soups; pour over first mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy ranch dressing
directions: Puree cottage cheese, buttermilk, lemon juice, horseradish, mustard, garlic, basil, oregano and pepper together in a blender. Serve 2 tablespoons over greens.

title: pauline's monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Thoroughly butter a tube pan.	Cut each biscuit into quarters and form into marble size balls.
Dip balls in melted butter, then in sugar and cinnamon.
Drop balls into tube pan, forming a layer.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Repeat to use all balls.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° to 400° about 15 minutes.

title: jungle fun toss
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Store in an airtight container. Makes 10 1/2 cups snack.

title: real good fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, add fruit salad, pineapple tidbits, mandarin oranges (drained), package of pudding and sliced bananas.
Stir ingredients and, if you would like, put maraschino cherry halves on top.

title: spicy fish dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, salad dressing, sour cream and mustard. Mix thoroughly. Fold in flaked fish. Chill overnight to blend flavors. Serve with chips, crackers or toasted party breads.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt; drain.
Add chili with beans, tomato sauce, pepper and sugar.
Simmer while cooking spaghetti. Layer in casserole first, half of spaghetti, then half of meat mixture.
Next, layer some Velveeta cheese slices, then rest of spaghetti and meat mixture.
Top with Velveeta slices.
Cut slice in small pieces.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet kisses
directions: Blend flour, butter, sugar, lemon rind and egg yolk.
Make small balls. Dip each in egg white and roll in chopped almonds. Place on a greased baking sheet.
Make a depression in each ball and bake in a 375° oven until lightly browned. Fill depressions with jam.
Makes 20 to 30 kisses.

title: double chocolate fudge squares
directions: In small bowl, mix flour and baking soda; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil; remove from heat.
Add 1 cup chocolate pieces and vanilla; stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a medium bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in remaining chocolate pieces and nuts.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: uncooked macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except boiled eggs.
Let stand in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan overnight.
Slice and add eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in microwave covered dish for about 6 minutes per pound.
Cool and chop; put in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Add celery, almonds, eggs and water chestnuts.
Mix together mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup and lemon juice.
Add mixture to chicken.
Sprinkle crushed chips over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: impossible garden pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: standing rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Place roast on grill pan and season. Cook fat side up.
Use garlic inserted into slits in the fat, freshly ground black pepper, paprika, seasoned meat tenderizer, etc.
Place in oven uncovered with a meat thermometer inserted into the center.
Cook 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° or 350°. Cook to your taste.
Medium-rare usually takes 2 hours.
Let stand about 15 minutes before cutting with an electric knife.
Mix au jus according to package directions.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cooled corn bread, add onions, peppers, tomatoes and celery; mix well.
Add mayonnaise and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Prepare 1 package jello
with
cup boiling water and 1/2 of fruit.
Refrigerate
until set.
Spread sour cream over congealed layer.
Repeat 1st layer and chill until firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls and press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: winter vegetable chowder(lo-fat)
directions: Bring 3 cups of water and salt to boiling in large saucepan. Peel parsnips, halve lengthwise and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Peel sweet potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Cut broccoli into stems and separate head into small flowerets. Peel stems and cut into 1/2-inch dice.
Add broccoli stems, parsnips, sweet potatoes and onion to boiling water.
Lower heat. Simmer 6 minutes.
Add broccoli flowerets; simmer 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine Ricotta cheese, milk, potato flakes, pepper, nutmeg and sugar in blender until smooth.
Stir Ricotta mixture into vegetable mixture in saucepan until blended. Gently heat through.
Ladle into soup bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: jamaican curry chicken
directions: Use any kind of chicken pieces, legs, thighs or breasts.
Cut peppers into strips and cook in a little oil in a large soup kettle until soft.
Add chicken, 1 cup liquid, tomatoes and seasonings (salt and pepper to taste).
Stir together.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.
Cover and let cook for approximately 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar, pecans and pineapple.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Before serving, add rest of ingredients.
This keeps well for several days in refrigerator, also freezes well.
Old family recipe used every Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: Sear chops on both sides.
Put in a roaster.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Top each chop with mixture.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: abe's favorite hamburgers
directions: Mix well and form into patties.
Put some butter and Worcestershire sauce in frypan and melt.
Add garlic salt and real garlic to this and fry burgers.
Top with Cheddar cheese until melted.

title: breakfast biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pan or spray with Pam cooking spray.
Spread biscuits on bottom and side of muffin pan to form cups.
Crumble and brown sausage; drain grease.
In separate pan, scramble eggs until almost done.
Add sausage and scramble until done.
Divide egg and sausage mix into biscuit cups and top with cheese.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until biscuits are done.
These are good to freeze and microwave later.

title: hot sauce
directions: Saute
onion
in
small
amount
of oil until soft; add Serrano
peppers;
brown.
Chop
tomatoes and cut up cilantro. Add to pepper and onion mixture.
Add garlic, salt and pepper. Cook until thick.
Enjoy with tostados; add to cheese, etc.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water. Slice strawberries, then stir into jello mixture.
Set aside. Cream sugar and butter.
Stir in coarsely crushed pretzels.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and 4 1/2 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Pour jello mixture over cream cheese.
Layer. Refrigerate.
Top with balance of Cool Whip.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients for a quick and delicious fruit salad.

title: sure fire pie crust
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Beat remaining ingredients together and fold into flour mixture.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for at least 15 minutes before rolling.
Will keep for about 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: taco season mix
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in jars for storage.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Combine nuts, sugar and coconut; add butter and milk. Mix well; chill. Form into balls; chill balls until firm. Melt paraffin and chocolate chips together in double boiler. Insert wooden picks into candy balls; dip into chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: play dough
directions: Place flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add olive oil and stir in.
Add desired food coloring to 1 cup of water.
Stir well.
Stir water into flour and salt mixture.
Use hands to mix in.
Gradually add water, a tablespoon at a time, mixing it in well, until a pliable dough has formed.
Makes about 4 cups of play dough.
Store in a zippered bag or tightly covered plastic bag.

title: bacon and cheese chowder
directions: Drain bacon on towel; add to drippings the onions, letting them brown slightly.
Add celery, potatoes and broccoli. Sprinkle with dill, salt and pepper.
Pour water over mixture. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in milk before soup reaches the boiling; stir in cheese.
Simmer until melted.
Serve with crumbled bacon on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring to boiling point, then mix with 1/3 pkg. herb stuffing mix.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Heat soup, milk, cheese, onion and butter.
Add cheese until soup is consistency you want it.
Do not make it too thick.
Add cooked broccoli.
Simmer a few minutes.
Taste improves when it is left in the refrigerator for a couple of days.

title: juicy soda
directions: Fill cup 1/3 full of juice and fill rest of way with plain or fruit flavored seltzer.

title: gelatin strawberries (candy)(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Mix together first the vanilla and almond extract. Mix milk, coconut, 1 package Jell-O, almonds, sugar and flavorings. Form into strawberry balls. Roll in remaining package of strawberry Jell-O. Allow to dry on wax paper and store in airtight containers. Do not refrigerate. Yields 25.

title: ginger tea punch
directions: Brew 2 cups of regular tea.
Cool slightly.
Add fruit juices and sugar.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over ice.

title: busy woman's egg brunch
directions: In a greased glass Pyrex dish, put broken up bread; cover with ham, sausage or bacon.
Beat eggs, milk, seasonings and cheese. Pour over bread and meat layers.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: black beans and rice
directions: In medium saucepan, combine broth, coconut and margarine. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in beans; cover and cook an additional 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: ritz cracker icebox fruit cake
directions: Cut in all ingredients.
Crumble crackers.
Mix well.
Heat milk in double boiler and melt marshmallows.
Pour over crackers and other ingredients.
Keeps well for weeks in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften.
Mix ingredients with cheese.
Shape and chill, then roll in chopped pecans.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in half lengthwise.
Hollow out and reserve 1/2 of zucchini insides.
Dice the reserved insides.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Mix apple juice, cream soda, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Pour over apple slices to coat well.
Pour filling into crust lined pie plate.
Top with remaining crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and apples are tender.

title: cajun fried chicken wings
directions: Preheat deep fryer to 350°.
Wash and split wings.
Season with spices to taste.
Coat with flour.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes.

title: rosettes
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt and milk.
Stir in flour gradually and beat until smooth.
Cover bowl and let stand for a while so bubbles will break down.
Dip iron in mixture; fry in hot oil until slightly light brown.
Sprinkle with sugar (optional).

title: bojangle's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients gently.
Roll out on wax paper, keeping dough about 1/2 to 1 inch thick.
Cut out with biscuit cutter. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Baste with butter before and after baking.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a saucepan.
Place over medium heat; bring to a hard boil and let boil 2 minutes. Remove from
heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla and blend well.
Drop teaspoonfuls of mixture onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm and cool.

title: velvet cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and cream well.
Add unbeaten egg and extracts.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to cream mixture, a little at a time.
Fill cookie press and form cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix
first 5 ingredients and form into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with tomato soup and 1 can of water. Cover dish and bake around 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries.
Add sugar and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour. Make jello.
Add berries and pineapple mixture together.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese, and sugar until very creamy. Add eggs gradually alternating with flour. Add lemon flavor and vanilla. Pour into a greased & floured bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cucumber-onion in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Cover and chill.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Use cool broth from chicken. Best to chill
dough, but not necessary.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar and refrigerate while mixing cake.
Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add egg yolks and blend on medium speed of mixer, then on lowest speed, add in flour, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Quickly add egg whites and fold in.
Bake in tube pan (10-inch)) at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: apple-walnut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine first 3 ingredients in medium bowl and mix until finely crumbled.
Stir in nuts.
Press cups of mixture evenly into bottom of prepared dish.
Add cinnamon, baking soda and salt to remaining mixture and blend well.
Beat in egg, sour cream and vanilla. Gently stir in apples.
Spoon evenly into dish.
Bake until cake begins to pull away from side of dish and tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely in pan.
Cut into squares.
Top with vanilla ice cream.

title: blackberry soup
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil, cover, lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool, 1/2 hour.
Press mixture through fine mesh strainer.
Chill until ready to use.
Then combine yogurt, sour cream and blackberry puree until smooth and silky.
Garnish with reserved berries or top with Creme Fraiche.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening and margarine together.
Then add both sugars; mix until well blended.
Add dry
pudding mix; blend.
Add eggs; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients and slowly stir into batter.
Stir in vanilla, then chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful onto greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, eggs, apples, raisins and pecans.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to mixture then add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 350° in well-greased tube pan.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water, dissolving fully.
Add juices; let set overnight.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Kool-Aid may be substituted according to color scheme.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Bland all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream the peanut butter, shortening, 1/3 cup sugar and brown sugar. Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine flour and soda.
Gradually add to creamed mixture. Blend thoroughly. Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ham & cheese ball
directions: Mix by hand softened cream cheese, ham, American cheese, onion and ketchup. Shape into ball. Cover with nuts or pecans if desired. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Mix and shape into rolls.
Wrap in foil or wax paper and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake 1 hour, unwrapped, on rack at 300°; turn once.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.
Heat apples and water to boiling.
Simmer until tender and smooth (approximately 10 to 20 minutes).
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add to apples.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; freeze, process to can, or cool and eat.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with all the ingredients.
Blend with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into pie shell (unbaked).
Bake in preheated oven at 400° about 30 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Double ingredients makes 3 pies.

title: jambolt
directions: Mix all together and bake until done at 350°, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Rinse cans with a little water.
Add seasonings.
Sprinkle in Romano, simmer for 1/2 hour.
Stir in 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.

title: punch
directions: Boil water; add sugar.
Mix the rest of ingredients together.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix sauces, marmalade and
brown sugar thoroughly.
Put in large saucepan or skillet and simmer.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into bite size balls. Bake 15 minutes in oven at 350° or lightly browned. Best served warm or at room temperature. Makes 30 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: spicy carrot bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and blend well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg and add to butter mixture.
Mix well. Stir in oats, carrots and nuts.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan (lightly greased).
Bake 25 minutes until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired. Cut into bars as desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and add onion and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally until beans are tender.

title: coconut macaroon cookies
directions: Form into desired size of cookie and press very flat with palm of hand for a good rich, crispy cookie.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Peel and chop peaches.
Mix other ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add peaches last.
Pour into churn and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute carrots and onion in oil in large nonstick saucepan until softened, 5 minutes.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons water if sticking.
Add garlic; saute 30 seconds.
Add beans, basil, oregano, tomatoes, tomato paste and mushrooms; simmer covered 25 minutes to mingle flavors.
Add broccoli; cook 5 minutes.
Add peppers.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; stir to mix well.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in oblong pan.
Put crushed pineapple over filling and crumble dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt oleo and dribble over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas fragrance(for smell only)
directions: Simmer on stove to add a wonderful Christmas fragrance all through the house.
Add water as it boils down.

title: quick microwave cobbler
directions: Mix cake mix with peach juice until good consistency. Add fruit; put in microwavable deep dish.
Put microwave on High; turn cake (or check it) every 3 minutes. Total cooking time about 12 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Fry onion, potato and carrot in oil until onion is golden brown and soft.
Add water, oregano, basil, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add zucchini and boil gently for 15 more minutes.
Add beans, tomatoes and spaghetti or macaroni.
Boil 12 to 15 minutes until spaghetti or macaroni is just cooked.

title: lumpia
directions: In a large saucepan, brown meat with garlic and onion.
Add vegetables and seasonings; cook for 2 minutes.
(Do not overcook vegetables.)
Drain and cool.
Combine flour and water to make a paste.
To make lumpia, place 2 tablespoons of vegetable filling on a wrapper.
Fold nearest edge of wrapper over filling; fold left and right towards center.
Roll tightly toward open edge.
Seal with paste.
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry lumpia until golden brown; drain.
Serve with Lumpia Dipping Sauce.
Makes 40 lumpia.

title: creamed thousand island dressing
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add lemon juice, oil, seasonings and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and refrigerate.
Fold in whipped cream just before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium and boil 3 to 4 minutes to soft ball stage, 234°. Remove and stir in the rest.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Combine cake mix, coconut and margarine.
Mix well and press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin oat streusel muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or lightly grease bottoms only.
Combine dry ingredients, including nuts.
Add pumpkin, milk, oil and egg; mix just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Sprinkle tops of muffins evenly with streusel mixture.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let muffins stand a few minutes; remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool on wire rack.

title: rancho grande
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add chopped onion to meat and cook 5 minutes.
Add 1 package chili seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Cook macaroni in salted water; drain.
Pour macaroni in bottom of greased baking dish.
Stir in meat sauce.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, butter and 1 1/4 cups chopped walnuts; mix well.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar until light. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk; beat until thick.
Spread on cream cheese layer. Spread remaining 1/4 cup nuts on top.

title: willa ogilvie's fudge
directions: Put margarine and chips in a very large bowl; set aside.
Mix together milk and sugar in a large saucepan; heat to boiling and boil for 7 minutes.
Pour boiled mixture over chocolate and margarine.
Add vanilla.
Beat by hand for 5 minutes or longer, making sure the chocolate chips and margarine are completely melted.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased pan or pans.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: In a bowl, stir together eggs, milk, onion, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir in ham.
Toss together cheese and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour mixture into hot pastry shell.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken-etti
directions: Cook spaghetti. Add the next eight ingredients and stir well. Add the grated cheese and stir until melted. Mix all ingredients on top of the stove.
Serve hot.

title: almond triangles
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Beat 1/2 pound butter, 1/2 cup granulated sugar, salt and almond extract.
Beat in egg and then flour.
Press dough into pan and push up sides. Refrigerate.
Heat oven to 375°.
Prick dough with fork and bake 10 minutes.

title: chocolate texas sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugar; set aside.
Combine in saucepan margarine, water, Crisco and cocoa.
Bring to a boil; pour this over flour and sugar and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: quick corn mazatlan
directions: Drain corn, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine reserved liquid and cream cheese in saucepan.
Heat and blend until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Cook 1 package of cranberries in 1 quart water until skins pop. Strain and add cranberry juice to 1 quart water and the rest of the ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.
Nice at Christmas and holiday time.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and bananas; mix well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Add nuts while folding in egg whites.
Bake in layers and use any cream filling desired.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine avocado (pitted), onion (minced), vinegar, salt and pepper to taste and chopped green chili.
Beat until smooth on medium mixer speed.
Finely chop 1/2 peeled ripe tomato; fold into mixture.
Serve guacamole as a dip with corn chips.

title: homestead succotash
directions: Cook bacon until
crisp,
drain.
Add onions and thyme. Cook until tender.
Stir in vegetables and heat through.

title: chili dip
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish stir together cheese and chili.
Microwave on Medium for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rotel-cheese potatoes
directions: Heat potatoes and
drain.
Make a sauce out of tomatoes and cheese.
Stir into potatoes.

title: mamaw's jam cake
directions: Roll apples, nuts and raisins in flour. Mix all and bake at 350°. It will make 4 layers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Pour into casserole dish. Pour soups over beef and onion.
Sprinkle cheese over beef, onion and soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake in 400° oven 30 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion until tender.
Boil chicken until done. Then cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix together oleo, onion, stuffing mix (without boxed seasoning); add sage.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom with chicken.
Layer in cake pan chicken mixture, then dressing; add slowly 2 cups broth.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: chop suey for 40
directions: Saute beef in oil with onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain any excess fat.
Add tomato soup, tomato paste and crushed tomatoes. Heat through.
In the meantime, cook the macaroni and drain.
Add the sauce to the macaroni.
Mix well.

title: fork cookies
directions: Mix and bake cookies at 375°.

title: microwave party mix
directions: Combine cereals, crackers, pretzels and nuts in a large glass, microwavable
bowl.
Mix
margarine
and seasonings in small bowl.
Pour over cereal mixture to coat well.
Microwave on
High for 4 minutes.
Stir once.	Spread on paper towels or put in paper bag to drain.
Cool.
Yields 3 to 4 quarts.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually until light and fluffy. Add beaten eggs.
Add spices, 1/2 of flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix remaining flour with pecans and fruit.
Mix all together.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: cheese ball with everything
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature.
In a large mixer bowl beat together cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Beat in Swiss and Cheddar cheeses, half the bacon, onion, half of the pecans, pimento, pickle relish, salt and pepper until combined.
Cover and chill for several hours or until firm.

title: macaroni and ground beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water.
Brown onion, pepper and meat in skillet in a small amount of fat.
Add soup, undiluted.
Add cooked macaroni, mushrooms and olives.
Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and cook in 325° oven 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Heat cream cheese in microwave to soften.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Let chill until firm; shape into one large ball or two small balls.
Roll in pecans to coat.

title: snackers
directions: Break crackers into four squares.
With a knife, spread peanut butter evenly over each square.
Cut marshmallows in half.
Place 1/2 of a marshmallow over peanut butter.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over cabbage and onion.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil; pour over cabbage and cover immediately.
Let stand a few hours.
This slaw keeps several days.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate. Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Stir in salt and pepper. Spread in plate.
In a bowl, beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth (1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour over hamburger mixture in plate.
Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (5 to 8 minutes). Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolatown cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, shortening, brown sugar, sugar, eggs, corn syrup, water and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Beat well; stir in Hershey's chips.
Drop by level 1/4 cupfuls 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: butterscotch apples
directions: Wash apples and cut into quarters.
Pare and core them.
Put sugar and water in a saucepan and heat; when syrup boils, add apples.
Cover and boil gently until apples are tender.
Remove apples from syrup; use skimmer or slotted spoon.
Place fruit in dishes for serving.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Yields 50 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: mandlebread
directions: Using electric mixer, beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt; blend well.
Add 1/4 cup oil; blend.
Stir in 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup nuts; blend.
Add remaining 1/4 cup oil, 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup nuts; blend.
Add remaining flour and baking powder and blend.
Add vanilla and optional chocolate chips.
Grease 2 large baking sheets.
Divide batter into 6 portions and spread dough onto baking sheets in loaf shapes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until edges are just brown.
Remove from oven; cool slightly and slice into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place pieces, cut side down, and bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: old-fashioned dumplings
directions: Mix all together just like you would for pie crust.
Then take enough cold water to mix.
Roll out thin and cut in strips.
Be sure to use hot broth.
Cook until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk bran pancakes
directions: Put liquid ingredients in blender first, then add dry ingredients and blend well.
Makes 8 (5-inch) pancakes.

title: our family potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk, and cream with milk.

title: chicken chinese
directions: Brown onion and celery in margarine.
Add chicken, soup, milk and water chestnuts.
Cover with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wayne's mushroom chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for at least 2 hours in the fridge.
Cook chicken on the grill or broil it in the oven.
Cook 7 minutes on one side, then turn for an additional 3 minutes.
Place mushrooms and cheeses on top and heat until cheeses are melted.

title: clam dip
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to boiling and simmer for 15 minutes. Add 1/2 cup plain bread crumbs.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream 2 cups sugar and butter.
Add milk alternately with 3 cups sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Add vanilla.
Fold in whites of 5 beaten eggs.
Add
1 cup hickory nuts.
Bake in layers.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, oleo and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop artichokes and mix in all other ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes, then 1 minute under the broiler. Serve warm with crackers.

title: oil fried doughnuts
directions: Place eggs in a large bowl; beat well.
Stir in orange juice, 1/4 cup oil and grated orange peel.
Mix in sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add and beat in flour.
Drop by teaspoon into deep hot 375° peanut oil.
Fry until well brown (about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on each side).
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Makes about 24.

title: taco beef dip
directions: Brown beef; break into bits.
Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Stir in water, beer and tomato paste.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add grated cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm, using tortilla chips for dipping.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy Dutch oven. Add onions and cook, stirring constantly, until golden. Sprinkle with flour.
Cook and stir until flour and onions are browned. Stir in consomme and water. Bring to a boil, then simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Drizzle melted butter on bread.
Place on soup; top with grated cheese. Brown under broiler or in microwave until cheese melts.

title: cilantro dip
directions: In small bowl, combine sour cream, cilantro, lemon juice, garlic and salt.
Chill until ready to serve.
With knife, slice top 1/3 off bread.
Hollow out inside, leaving 1/2-inch shell. Cut bread from inside into 2-inch cubes to use.
Fill hollowed bread with chilled dip.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on croissants.

title: june's yummy pecans
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large frying pan until glazed. Use medium heat.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Then broil 2 to 3 minutes, watching carefully.

title: peppy sandwich spread
directions: Mix cheese food and cream cheese until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for dip or spread on sandwiches.

title: pistachio fluffy frosting
directions: Pour the milk into a large mixing bowl.
Add the heavy cream and add the package of pistachio pudding and pie filling.
Beat slowly, gradually increasing speed to high and whip until mixture will form soft peaks.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Spoon ice cream by tablespoons into large punch bowl.
Add water and lemonade concentrate; stir until just combined.
Slowly pour carbonated beverage down side of bowl.
Stir gently to mix. Makes 24 (6 ounce) servings or 32 (4 ounce) servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in the 2 cups of water until puffed and soft. Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add to raisins and 1 teaspoon of lemon juice.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, chicken broth and water in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly.

title: marinated pork roast
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, garlic, mustard, ginger and thyme. Place roast in large clear plastic bag.
Set in deep bowl to steady roast.
Pour in marinade and close bag tightly.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator. Occasionally press bag against meat in several places to distribute marinade evenly.
Remove meat from marinade.
Place roast on rack in shallow pan.
Roast uncovered in slow oven (325°) 2 1/2 to 3 hours until thermometer registers 175°.
Baste occasionally with marinade during last hour of roasting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs to mixture.
Beat. Put pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients together for 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with juice for thickening.
Add when ready to thicken. Add pineapple chunks last.

title: easy fruit dessert or salad
directions: Combine all fresh fruits with peach pie filling and refrigerate until chilled and ready to serve.
Can be used as a salad or dessert.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, when brown add beans and tomato soup.
Let simmer while the potatoes are cooking.
Put mixture into an oven proof casserole or baking dish.
Using an ice cream scoop or a large spoon, place scoops on top of the beef mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk with wire whisk.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Hold cupcake, top side down in palm of hand.
Spread whipped topping on bottom and sides.
Press coconut over frostings.
Place cupcakes, top side down, on serving platter.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 24 snowballs.

title: fruited yogurt dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese at medium speed until fluffy.
Add next 3 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and coconut.
Serve with fruit.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chip toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Beat eggs until foamy. Add flour and sugars; beat until well blended. Blend in butter, chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake approximately 30 to 35 minutes. Very rich.

title: mom's penuche
directions: Cook sugar and milk together, stirring until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat when soft ball is formed, when dropped in cold water; add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until candy begins to hold its shape.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased sheet.
When set, remove to airtight container.

title: chicken cacciatore casserole
directions: Spread rice in bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon parsley and remaining ingredients, except chicken and cheese.
Pour over rice.

title: peg's pizza pie casserole
directions: Cook meat in a skillet with garlic until browned.
Remove with slotted spoon and add to cooked, drained noodles in a casserole dish.

title: pecan roll
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, kneading in the powdered sugar. Shape into 8 rolls, 1 inch in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze overnight.

title: stay together meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: garlic pork roast
directions: Using the point of a paring knife, make slits all around the roast.
Insert garlic into slits.
Rub roast with salt and sprinkle pepper.
Place in a roasting pan and insert a meat thermometer.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes per pound or until thermometer registers 160° to 170°.
Remove from pan and let stand.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix and put into tube pan.
Bake
1 hour at 300°.
Cool for a few minutes.
Remove cake from pan, leaving tube in pan.

title: corn dip
directions: Dice tomatoes and onion; mix everything together. Chill. Serve with Fritos (Big Scoop).

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy; add water, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Makes 2 (9 x 9-inch) cakes.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: prune cake(moist and flavorful)
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and salad oil.
Mix flour with soda, salt and spices and alternate with the buttermilk.
Last, add the nut meats and vanilla.
Bake in an angel food cake pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in salt water until tender.
Cool.
Drain and cut in small pieces.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Fold in chicken, celery, pineapple, carrots and almonds.
Serve on lettuce leaf and garnish with Mandarin orange slices, if desired.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook a chicken, then tear the meat from the bone.
Boil noodles according to the package.
Then mix the Ro-Tel tomatoes and cubed Velveeta cheese together with the chicken and spaghetti. Add milk if difficult to mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until heated all the way through.

title: peach crumble
directions: Place peaches on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle on peaches and drizzle butter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm or cold.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine corn kernels, tomato, pepper, onion, cheese and cornmeal.
Let stand 30 minutes. Turn into buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown pork and beef in Dutch oven.
Add onion and tomatoes. Add bay leaf, oregano, salt and parsley.
Cover and simmer 4 hours.
Uncover and add tomato paste.
Remove meat and simmer until thick.
May be frozen for future use.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: Mix together.
Dip sliced bread in mixture and fry on each side until golden brown on both sides.
Sprinkle a lot of powdered sugar on top of each slice.
May be also served with syrup.

title: cucumber tomato salad
directions: Cut all vegetables in chunks.
Pour dressing over top, sprinkle with pepper if desired.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled before serving.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Brown chicken and pork in oil.
Add all other ingredients and simmer at least one hour.
Remove as much fat as possible.
Stir in coconut creme just before serving.

title: indian salmon croquettes
directions: In large bowl, drain and pulverize salmon.
Add all ingredients except olive oil, flour and chutney.
Mix thoroughly. Mixture should be moist and not too chunky.
Pour a couple of tablespoons of olive oil into a heavy seasoned iron skillet and heat over medium flame.
Shape croquettes to desired size, dust with flour on both sides and cook, turning until both sides are golden brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot with a dollop of chutney.

title: rice consomme
