directions: Mix all ingredients and bake covered at 325° for 1 hour.
You can use a margarine substitute and this is a very low calorie, but delicious casserole.
You can make it ahead.

title: quick red velvet cake
directions: Place a rack in the center of the oven and preheat the oven to 350°. Generously grease two 9-inch round cake pans with solid vegetable shortening, then dust with flour.
Shake out excess flour.
Set the pans aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Put into baking dish.
Add cheese.
Bake until hot.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix by directions on box, using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Cool cake completely.
Add coconut cream on top of cake.
Then spread 1 can condensed milk on coconut cream.
Add Cool Whip on top of milk and then sprinkle coconut over top.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brown sugar cookies(no eggs)
directions: Bake on cookie sheet 5 to 8 minutes at 300° or until brown. Cut into cookies.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on stove for 2 to 3 hours on medium heat.

title: mediterranean salad
directions: Combine lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, olives and cheese in large bowl.
Whisk olive oil, vinegar and oregano in small bowl until well blended.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over salad and toss to coat evenly.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: grape juice lemonade
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given.
Chill for 1/2 hour. Serve in each glass a thin slice of lemon from which the seeds have been removed.
This quantity will serve 6 water glasses or 18 punch glasses.

title: ground chuck casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck in oven skillet.
Put Tater Tots on top of meat, then mix mushroom soup with some milk.
Pour over meat and Tater Tots.
Put frozen onion rings on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, oleo and powdered sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Edge up slightly on sides.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Remove and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crust. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together until doughy consistency.
Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: texas gold bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter, and 1 egg.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Let cool; cut into bar shapes.

title: italian tomato salad
directions: Use 9 or 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Slice tomatoes about 1/3-inch thick and put one layer in plate.
Slice the onion very thin and put on tomatoes.
Cut sweet pepper in strips and arrange in layers.
Cut hot pepper and put a few here and there.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on bottom of glass pie plate. Spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave about 2 minutes until cheese on top melts.
Serve with nachos.
May be made a day ahead.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Thaw pink lemonade concentrate.
Add sweetened condensed milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Keep refrigerated.
(You can add food coloring, if you like.)

title: marty's deer chili
directions: Note:
To make it hotter, throw in cayenne or jalapeno peppers.

title: chocolate crisps
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the flour, cocoa powder, salt, baking soda and sugar. In a small bowl, mix the egg white, oil, vanilla and water. Add wet ingredients to the dry ingredients all at once. Mix well, then roll the dough in your hands into 1 1/2-inch thick "snake". Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 350° and spray baking sheet with pan spray. Slice the chilled dough into 1/4-inch thick rounds. Arrange the cookies 1-inch apart on the baking sheet. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes. Makes 30.

title: hamburg and bean sprouts
directions: In electric skillet, brown green pepper. Add hamburg and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat until gravy and bean sprouts get hot.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: baked clams oregano
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wash and open clams, removing one side of shell from each.
Place in baking dish.
Mix onion, breadcrumbs, garlic, oregano and oil and spoon over each clam until all is used up.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until breadcrumbs turn golden brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken until done.
Cool and remove all meat from bones. Save broth to use to cook spaghetti for richer flavor.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in oleo.
Add diced chicken, eggs and pimentos.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and add to other ingredients with mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Put in casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: frozen p.t.a.  slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mash bananas in blender and add rest of the ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Add 7-Up and serve slushy.
You may have to break up frozen chunks.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple and blueberries with juice.
Pour in 9 1/2 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Refrigerate to congeal.

title: breaded ranch chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine corn flakes, cheese and dressing mix. Dip chicken in butter, then coat with flakes. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear. Serves 8.

title: basic italian cookies
directions: Blend sugar and baking powder with the flour with a wire whisk.
Put on a pastry board; make a well in the center of the flour mixture.
Break the eggs into the center and add the vanilla.

Knead the dough well for 5 minutes until it is smooth, adding a little flour if the dough seems too sticky and soft. Pinch off bits of dough about the size of a small apricot and form into desired shape (rings or strips).
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in a hot 450° oven for 10 minutes or less until golden.
Watch carefully, because they brown easily! Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: foil-baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange fish fillet on aluminum foil. Spread mushrooms over fish.
Combine butter, onion, thyme, salt and pepper over fish.
Wrap up tightly.
Seal ends well.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: ground turkey loaf
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a medium bowl; mix well. Place mixture on a greased broiler rack and shape into a slightly rounded loaf (mixture will be soft).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: gail's quick potato soup
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan put potatoes, onions and water.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Slightly mash potatoes with a fork to thicken soup.
Add milk and rest of ingredients.
Heat; do not boil.

title: quick and easy pizza
directions: Spread sauce on English muffins.
Sprinkle diced Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese over sauce.
Bake or broil until bubbling and cheese is melted.

title: kahlua caramel popcorn
directions: In a shallow pan, keep popped corn warm in low oven.
Bring sugar, Kahlua and vinegar to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add butter.
Insert candy thermometer and cook to hard crack stage (300°).
Pour over warmed, popped corn and stir to coat evenly.
Add nuts.
Cool and store in airtight container in cool place.

title: damson jelly
directions: Place damsons in saucepan with 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Run through sieve and add water to make 5 1/2 cups juice.
Place juice in 8-quart pot with margarine and pectin; bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly. Quickly add sugar and bring back to a full, rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: gumbo
directions: Fry bacon and ham together until well done.
Remove the meat and add flour to the grease (add additional oil if needed).
Cook to golden brown.
Add green peppers, onions, green onions, celery, garlic, okra and sufficient liquid to wilt all vegetables.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Place all the cooked ingredients into a large pot and add additional liquid, bay leaves, parsley and tomato paste and cook about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sausage and cook for about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, crabs and crabmeat and simmer for 30 minutes.
During this last 30 minutes, salt and pepper to taste and add oysters if desired.
Makes approximately 2 gallons.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Blend all ingredients, then combine with shrimp and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to cook, place a sheet of aluminum foil over the grill.
Poke it with small holes.
Spread the shrimp over the foil and cover.
Baste generously with marinade and turn frequently.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
Peel and eat.

title: chuckwagon stew
directions: Wash and pat dry meat. Brown in pam in a 5 quart pot. Add seasoning, tomatoes, broth and veggies to meat. Cover and simmer for 2-2 1/2
hours. Use arrowroot per directions to thicken.

title: mom's baked lasagne
directions: In shallow baking dish, arrange alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Add enough flour so dough is not sticky. Oil bowl.
Turn rolls over 1 time.
Let rise until double in size. Punch down and make into balls the size of a walnut.
Put a pat of butter on each ball.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: penny's porcupine balls
directions: Mix all together and form into meat balls.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour 1 can tomato soup and 1 cup water that has been mixed together over top of meat balls.
Makes its own gravy.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in egg yolks.
Mix fruit and nuts.
Sprinkle half of flour over fruits and nuts (mix).
Mix with butter and sugar.
Add rest of flour.
Beat egg whites separately and fold into cake mixture.
Add extract.
Bake in greased and wax paper lined pan.
I use my hands to mix all of this after I cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spinach souffl quiche
directions: Mix all together and turn into an unbaked deep-dish pie crust. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes or until it looks set in the middle.

title: lemon lush
directions: Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix together instant pudding and milk.
When thick, pour over cream cheese/Cool Whip layer.
Top with 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Line Pyrex dish with 1 to 1 1/2 inches of cooked rice.
Top each pork chops with 1 thick slice of onion, 1 slice bell pepper and 1 slice of fresh tomato.
Pour beef broth over all.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine well beaten egg, orange juice and cooking oil.
Mix well and add egg mixture all at once.
Mix only to dampen.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.

title: chicken divan
directions: Chop broccoli into flowerets and bite size stem pieces.
Steam until barely tender.
Gently fry chicken.
Place broccoli in a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Scatter chicken on top.

title: beef chili(30 minutes)
directions: Heat oil in deep, large skillet over medium heat 5 minutes. Meanwhile, cut each beef steak lengthwise into 1-inch wide strips, then cut crosswise in 1-inch pieces.
Sprinkle beef with 2 teaspoons Spicy Seasoning Mix.
Stir-fry beef and onion 2 to 3 minutes.
Season with salt, if desired.
Add tomatoes (break up with back of spoon), corn and remaining 2 1/2 teaspoons Spicy Seasoning Mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together the sugar and cocoa powder. Stir in evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until mixture is boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Serve warm over ice cream or sliced pound cake.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of sauce.

title: my favorite snack:  rice pudding
directions: Get a pot.
Mix it all together.
Heat until mix thickens. Cool and serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle onion soup in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with rice. Combine water with mushroom soup and pour over rice.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: white grape cooler
directions: Prepare juice concentrate according to directions on can; stir in white grape juice, lemon juice and honey.
Divide mixture among 6 tall glasses.
Add carbonated beverage.
Top with scoops of sherbet.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant casserole(for dieters.  origin of recipe: from "weight watchers".)
directions: Parboil eggplant 6 minutes.
Drain and put in a bowl.
Arrange in a casserole, eggplant and mixture, in layers, starting and ending with mixture.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 4 as a side dish.

title: chocolate oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream together 1 cup butter and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and 2 teaspoons of vanilla. Sift together flour, baking soda and 1 teaspoon salt. Add oats.

title: creamed corn(ala ruth)
directions: Cut corn off cob to about 3/4 of the ear's depth.
Remove remaining corn from cobs with a flat blade knife by scraping the cob.
Yield approximately
5 cups corn.
Stir in milk, salt, sugar and pepper until blended.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until corn is tender.

title: hot party dip
directions: Brown ground beef, keeping it crumbly.
In a saucepan, heat cheese until it melts.
Add chilies, drained tomatoes and browned meat. Serve hot as a dip with tortilla chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 15 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy and place in baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and melted oleo.
Pour over hominy.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar turkey casserole
directions: Prepare rice.
Fluff cooked rice with fork and spread into greased baking dish.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix with rice. Spread peas over rice.
Top with turkey.
Blend soup with milk to thin.
Pour evenly over turkey.
Sprinkle crumbs over mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: beet pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold liquid and flavoring.
Stir in the beets and pineapple.
Pour into a mold and chill.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar, add egg, then sifted flour, spices and baking powder and soda.
Add raisins and soup alternately.
Bake in a slow oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cupcakes if preferred; bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix crust ingredients and press into bottom of 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Finely grate the cheese.
Place all the ingredients in a bowl and blend together with fingers until smooth. Chill for 1 hour. Take chilled mixture and form into 1/2-inch size balls.
Place on baking sheet and chill for 1/2 hour.
Place baking sheet in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spicy beans & rice
directions: Combine beans, Rotel and water in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and with fork stir in the uncooked rice.
Cover and let steep for five minutes.

title: 7 layer jelly cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix well the sugar, eggs, milk, oil and flavoring.
Add flour until consistency is a little thicker than pancake batter.

title: stewed cabbage
directions: Fry bacon so that it's brown and crisp.
Save 2 to 3 tablespoons of bacon fat for flavoring.
Cut cabbage into large chunks.
Add cabbage, bacon fat, water and vinegar all in a crock-pot.
Mix, then crumble the bacon on top.
Cover and stew on low-medium for 4 hours.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil ingredients together until it spins a thread.
Add 1/4 teaspoon soda and 1/4
teaspoon
salt.
Pour over 1 gallon popcorn.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Saute with green onions in 4 tablespoons butter.
Stir in stuffing, chicken broth, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture and place in pie pan with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: smoked salmon spread(servings:  24)
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Blend first seven ingredients in a mixer.
Stir in salmon, celery and onion.
Yields about 3 cups (24 servings at 65 calories per serving).

title: italian zucchini casserole(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Fry loose sausage in large pot for 15 minutes and drain.
Peel zucchini and cut into bite-size chunks.
Boil for 5 minutes and drain well.
Push sausage to one side of pot.
Add butter and saute onion and pepper.
Add zucchini and the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into shallow casserole dish, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and margarine until crumbly.
Add eggs, water and lemon juice.
Makes 6 x 6-inch pie shell.

title: very special hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with crackers.
At any rate, you won't believe the taste combination.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hawaiian curry
directions: Bone chicken in small pieces.
Saute onion in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, curry powder and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Add 8 3/4 cups of broth and return to heat.
Stir constantly until sauce is thickened.
Pour over rice.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1x1 1/2 inch pieces.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Put the Cracker Barrel cheese as the topping.
Let juices cook out, then put dish in oven until cheese melts.
Very good.

title: spiced whipped cream topping
directions: Combine all ingredients and whip at high speed for 4 minutes or until whipping cream takes shape.
Chill.
Spoon over cooled pumpkin pie.

title: pam's fantasy fudge
directions: Add together the butter, sugar and evaporated milk. Bring to a boil. Stir well and continue boiling for about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in the chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and chopped pecans. Pour evenly in a 12 x 6 x 2 pan, smoothing out. Place in refrigerator until it hardens. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: dream date bars
directions: Combine butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar and sifted 1 1/4 cups flour.
Place in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: tomato soup with veal meatballs
directions: Heat olive oil in a large stock pot over moderate heat for 1 minute. Add carrot, onion and parsley. Reduce heat to low.
Cook, uncovered, until vegetables are soft, 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and chicken stock.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine the Crisco and one cup of flour.
Add ice water and enough remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Place on floured wax paper and knead until very stiff.
Divide into 2/3 piece and 1/3 piece.
Roll larger piece to extend 1/2-inch over rim of pie plate.
Place apples in plate.

title: key lime pie
directions: Prepare or purchase a 9-inch pie crust (regular or graham cracker).

title: old-fashioned gingerbread with orange cream frosting
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add egg and molasses, mixing well.

title: mel's louisiana shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add cold water.
In a large skillet, heat two inches of oil. Dip shrimp in batter.
With fork, put shrimp in hot oil, one at a time.
Cook 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve and eat hot.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In large bowl layer in order given, making sure mayonnaise mix covers the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight and next day until serving time.
Mix it all up just before serving.

title: egg strata
directions: Combine in a bowl 8 pieces of cooked bacon, 2 tablespoons margarine and 1/2 cup dried bread crumbs.
In another bowl, soak 2 cups bread crumbs and 1 3/4 cups milk.
Beat 8 eggs, salt and pepper; cook in 4 tablespoons margarine until barely beginning to set.
(Can use microwave.)
Add soaked bread crumbs and put in 9-inch greased casserole.
Sprinkle on top:
1 cup shredded sharp cheese, bacon and bread crumb mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Make ahead and refrigerate until ready to bake.

title: penne with vodka and tomato cream sauce
directions: Melt butter with oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until translucent, about 8 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook until almost no liquid remains in pan, stirring frequently about 25 minutes.
Add cream, vodka and red pepper and boil until thickened to sauce consistency, about 2 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, but still firm to bite, stirring to prevent sticking.
Drain well.
Transfer to large bowl.
Bring sauce to simmer.
Pour over pasta and toss well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients, then add ketchup last.
Let it stand in refrigerator for several hours to marinate.

title: golden corn and broccoli
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broccoli and water over high heat; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover.
Cook 8 minutes or until broccoli is tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain in colander.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 8 x 8-inch baking pan.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cream cheese, chopped ham and onion together.
Roll in chopped mixed nuts in the shape of a ball.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for one week.

title: fantasy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: tuna or chicken special casserole
directions: If you use chicken, add sage to taste.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes into fairly small cubes (about 1/2-inch).
Boil in salted water until they are tender but firm. Drain and let cool for a few minutes.
Add chopped boiled eggs, relish, pimentos and mayonnaise.
Mix.
Add just enough mustard to give a pleasant yellow color.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Good hot or cold and easy to make!

title: the witches brew
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Freeze until slushy.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together; add enough water to make a paste.
Add beaten egg yolks; mix well.
Heat remaining water with butter and salt until butter is melted.
Combine water and cocoa mixture; cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; mix well.
Let cool and pour into pie shell.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper.
Drain and sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Place in a large kettle.
Add tomato sauce with 1 can of water.
Add corn, chili and salsa. Heat slowly, stirring often.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and margarine. Boil for 8 to 9 minutes. Remove from heat; add chips and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Do not refrigerate. Keep covered.

title: mandarin almond salad
directions: In small skillet, melt 3 tablespoons sugar over low heat (patience!).
Add almonds; stir until coated.
Cool; break into small pieces and set aside.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine oil, vinegar, parsley, salt, pepper, hot pepper sauce and remaining sugar; shake well.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo and pour in square baking dish or pan.
Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pour over the melted oleo or butter.
Drain fruit of your choice and pour on top. (Blackberries need to be drained partly and add sugar to taste before adding to cobbler.
I do not drain peaches.) Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hawaiian milk punch
directions: Use large mixing bowl.
Soften sherbet.
Gradually add fruit juices.
Add milk.
Beat until frothy.
Serve in chilled bowl. Serves 30.

title: harvard hot pot
directions: Slice onions and green pepper and cook in margarine until tender.
Remove onion mixture and ground beef.

title: peanut popcorn balls
directions: Keep popped corn crispy in 300° oven.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Immediately pour over warm popcorn; mix gently to coat.
With buttered hands, form into 10 popcorn balls.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Line dish with meat seasoned with salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, then salt.
Add onions, then salt.
Pour soup over this. Add cheese.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: lipton roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan; discard bag.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish if desired with chopped parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage. Drain and crumble. Mix all ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350 degrees for 30 - 40 minutes. Canned onion rings may be added to the top the last few minutes.

title: cowboy dish
directions: Brown meat and drain fat;
add rest of ingredients except celery.
Simmer until heated and flavored thoroughly.
About 5 minutes before serving add diced celery.

title: sourdough refrigerator biscuits
directions: Grease a 10-cup plastic container with a tight fitting lid; set aside.
Sprinkle yeast over water.
Set aside to soften 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Use a pastry blender or two knives and cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.

title: raisin pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, spice and salt.
In another large bowl mix together eggs, pumpkin, oil and cereal.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture, mixing just until combined.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Pour mixture evenly into a 10 x 4-inch tube pan or a 12-cup Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for about 65 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely and remove from pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Need a sandwich maker for this!

title: spinach and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook spinach and broccoli together and drain well.
Mix sour cream and onion soup mix together and stir in the vegetables. Place
in
x
13-inch greased baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Work with hands to make smooth mixture; shape into 1-inch balls.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers and onion with salt; let stand 2 hours. Drain well.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Put in cartons and freeze.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet; season with basil, salt and pepper.

title: meatball sub casserole
directions: Mix green onions, bread crumbs, parmesan cheese and beef. Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on rack in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Arrange bread in a single layer in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan (all the bread may not be used).
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, Italian seasoning, and pepper.
Spread over the bread.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup mozzarella.
Combine sauce, water, and garlic; add meatballs.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining mozzarella.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Beat with beater until stiff.

title: dumplings
directions: Knead dough; roll thin.
Let stand for 2 or 3 hours.
Boil gently in chicken broth for 20 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup sweet milk.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Generously grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
In medium bowl with fork, mix well salmon, bread crumbs, eggs, onion and 1/3 cup undiluted cream of celery soup.
Spoon salmon mixture into loaf pan, press evenly into pan.
Bake in 375° oven 50 to 55 minutes until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
To serve, invert loaf into warm platter.
In 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat remaining undiluted soup and water to boiling; pour over loaf serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 8 servings, 245 calories per serving.

title: crater gravy
directions: Over heat mix margarine and flour.
Stir in beef broth; add water.
Cook down; add soup.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: pepper slaw
directions: Toss vegetables together in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Toss to mix, refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix together. Then add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon; mix well. Pour into ungreased loaf pans and bake for 45 minutes to an hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix corn flakes and butter and put on top.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with sour cream.
Pour in salsa.
Scatter pepper, onion and tomato.
Scatter Mozzarella, then Cheddar cheese.
Chill for 1 hour.
Good with tortilla chips.

title: fancy baked chicken
directions: Pour cold water over dried beef, drain and arrange in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken breasts over beef, top each half with slice of bacon (already cooked).
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream, pour over chicken.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: salty peanut cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Set aside. Cream together sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Mix well. Then add one at a time the oatmeal, peanuts and corn flakes.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet the size of a walnut about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: gretchen's homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook meat and onion together. Drain. Drain canned vegetables. Mix everything together and cook on stove for a few hours. Serve with Jiffy cornbread.

title: applesauce drop cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook
squash in enough boiling water to cover in saucepan
for 10
to
minutes or until tender; drain and mash. Combine
egg and 1 cup mashed squash.
Stir into dry ingredients
in
bowl. Add
onion and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons into shallow hot oil in skillet. Cook and brown on both sides. Drain on paper toweling.

title: tofu spread
directions: Steam carrots and let cool.
Make salad dressing by mixing vinegar, oil, mustard and spices.
Mash tofu with fork and mix with dressing.
Let marinate for 10 minutes.
Chop cooled carrots. Mix all together and add mayonnaise and/or sour cream.

title: easy cream puffs
directions: In saucepan bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and mix with wooden spoon.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Spoon onto cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and sugar; mix until well blended.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, cut into bars.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: The day before, mix the drained pineapple and marshmallows together.
Refrigerate.

title: moonwiches
directions: This is really simple, but it's a favorite.

title: easy delicious chili dip
directions: Press softened cream cheese into a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour can of chili on top.
Top this with taco cheese.
Cover dip with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 4 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: salsa mexicana
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Yields 3 cups.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla, cocoa and milk; mix well.
Mix in slowly the flour, soda and salt. Blend good.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Over chocolate chips and nuts, sprinkle 3 to 4 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in well-greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate rum angel
directions: Blend first four ingredients in top of double boiler and cook over simmering water, stirring until mixture is of custard consistency and coats a spoon, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marla's chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°. Drop teaspoons of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar, shape into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: plan ahead beef stew
directions: Combine beef, carrots, potato, onion, salt, pepper, bay leaf, soup and water in baking dish.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours or 200° for 8 hours.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk until pudding stage.
Fold in sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Make layers of vanilla wafers, bananas, pudding, until pudding is used up.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.

title: seafood eggplant casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash eggplant.
In skillet, saute onions, green peppers and butter until vegetables are soft.
Add shrimp, crabmeat, bread crumbs and eggs (slightly beaten) into buttered casserole.
Top with more bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 250° for one hour.
Serves 10.

title: apple peanut butter crunch
directions: Cut butter and peanut butter into combined oats, flour, sugar and salt.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and water.
Spoon peanut butter mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve hot or cold with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Stir in candied fruit and nuts.
Add Karo, sugar, lemon juice and rind (if desired) to beaten egg; mix well.
Stir in flour-fruit mixture.
Divide dough in half and turn out on well-greased and floured baking sheets. Moisten hands and flatten to 1/8-inch thickness (dough will rise during baking).
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube or 10-inch tube pan.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.
In a large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour half the batter into prepared pan.
Spread with sugar mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan 25 minutes.
Turn onto serving plate.
Makes 16 servings.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mix the next 5 ingredients.
In a large dish, place a layer of squash, then a layer of mixture, then sprinkle half of the herb stuffing.
Start with another layer of each.
Put stuffing last, then the stick of butter on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir together and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites in a small mixing bowl and set aside.
In large bowl, mix 2 sticks oleo, sugar, egg yolks and buttermilk.
Alternately add flour mixture, then add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Put in greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: red deviled eggs
directions: Marinate the eggs in pickled beet juice for at least 10 hours. Cut the eggs in half with sharp, clean knife.
Remove yolks and reserve egg whites. Blend with fork the yolks with mayonnaise, mustard, salt, parsley and sour cream.
Place in pastry tube and swirl the yolk in the red whites.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix all ingredients except berries until moistened. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Stir in drained berries. Spread batter into two 9-inch cake pans.

title: south carolina cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with buttermilk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Heat a 9-inch cast-iron skillet (put a little oil in skillet) in a 450° oven. Pour mix in skillet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Take out and turn cornbread over and bake another 12 to 15 minutes.

title: iced brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add cocoa and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and milk; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: salmon spread
directions: In bowl, blend all ingredients until well mixed.
Shape into a ball.
If mixture is too soft to hold shape, refrigerate several hours.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm cracked wheat crackers.

title: burgers florentine
directions: Prepare spinach as label directs and drain well.
Toast English muffins; keep warm.

title: johnson girls rocky road
directions: Place chocolate chips, butter and shortening in large, micro-proof bowl.
Microwave at Medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes or until chips are softened and mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts; blend well.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil. Stir until moistened.
Do not use mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Add bananas.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tested done.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: whole wheat hazelnut waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
Combine all dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In smaller bowl, combine yogurt, milk and melted butter.
Beat egg yolks until foamy and add to yogurt, milk and butter.
Mix wet ingredients gently into dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and fold carefully into batter. Spoon just enough batter into preheated waffle iron to cover the bottom.
Cook until waffle is golden brown.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small saucepan; bring mixture to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Let cool completely.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and toss lightly.
Pour marinade over vegetable mixture, stir gently. Cover salad and refrigerate overnight. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: baked beans and pineapple
directions: Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and shortening until butter is softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until done. Remove and cool.
If desired, you may ice the cookies.
Makes 36 to 48.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites, baking powder and salt until thick.
Beat in sugar until meringue holds a peak.
Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and butter.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top hot cake with Coconut Topping.

title: pretzels with onion soup
directions: Break pretzels into small pieces.
Melt margarine and add onion soup.
Stir and pour over pretzels.
Bake on cookie sheet at 250° for 15 minutes.
Take out; stir.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: whiskey sour slush
directions: Combine all liquid ingredients. Freeze overnight (or keeps for several months, covered, and frozen).
Remove 1 to 2 hours before party. Stir occasionally. Serve in punch bowl with oranges and cherries. Best served at slush consistency.

title: cornbread squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat just until moistened.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bread tests done.
Yields 9 servings.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Chop onion, olives and jalapenos and mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Spread on tortilla.
Roll up and place on a moist paper towel, seam side down.
Cover with moist paper towel to keep tortillas moist.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours and serve with salsa for dipping.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put raisins and egg whites in last.
Separate eggs and beat whites of eggs stiff.
Fold in last.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beer cheese spread
directions: Place all ingredients (except beer) in mixer. Gradually add beer.
Beat until smooth and fluffy. Store in covered bowl and refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.
Yields 1 quart.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pour in milk. Put butter in center of mixture.
Heat on Full power 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir well.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Blend smoothly first 4 ingredients; divide into 2 bowls.
Mix 1 portion with cocoa.
Mix other portion with diced almonds. Spread chocolate portion in baked pie shell, then put almond portion on top of first portion.
Refrigerate overnight.
Ready to serve next day.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions, pepper and sugar in corn oil until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Add bouillon and salt; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Pour into flame-proof soup tureen or individual casserole dishes.
Top with French bread and sprinkle generously with cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Makes 6 hearty servings.

title: meal soup
directions: Boil pieces of meat until tender.
Set aside 2 cups of the stock.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut each slice of
bacon into 3 pieces.
Spread a small amount of peanut butter
on
each	piece.	Roll
up and secure with toothpicks.
Microwave for	3 to 4 minutes until bacon is done. Delicious!

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies and nuts.
Add marshmallows last.
Mix well and drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cream soda cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions and cool.
Mix 2 boxes jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Mix well.
Add cream soda. Make holes in cake with toothpick and pour over cake.
Cool cake. Make vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Beat whipping cream in a different bowl until stiff.
Fold pudding and cream together. Spread over cake.
Garnish with nuts.

title: classic baked mostaccioli
directions: In large skillet, stirring frequently, brown beef, onion and garlic over medium heat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water. Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir about 1 cup of sauce over mostaccioli mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and half cup Parmesan.
Top with 2 cups of the sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Easily frozen and reheated.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; place in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Crumble 1 package of Waverly or Ritz crackers.
Add enough melted butter to moisten cracker crumbs.
Spread crumbs on top of vegetables; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in fruit; pour halve of gelatin in large Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until firm. Spread congealed gelatin in 1 cup sour cream.
Spoon remaining gelatin over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.
Top with remaining sour cream, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: squash and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Boil squash and onion in small amount of salted water until barely tender. Drain. While squash is cooking, prepare topping. Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet. Saute crushed crackers in butter until crisp and browned. Set aside. Make a white sauce using the 1/4 c. butter, cornstarch and half and half. Add cheese. Stir until sauce is smooth. Arrange squash in 9 X 13 glass baking dish. Pour sauce over squash. Top with cracker topping. Bake 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: oriental shrimp salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, blend the Italian dressing, soy sauce and ginger.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and chill. Serves 6.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Combine in order listed.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie dish.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Firm in middle when knife comes out clean.
To prevent burning of crust, cover crust with foil the entire time of baking.

title: almond punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in gallon jar.
Let punch chill overnight in the refrigerator, and it's ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, margarine, shortening, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake until lightly brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Crumble cake mix and butter.
Beat 1 egg and add to cake mixture.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake mixture. Bake at 325°, if using a glass pan.
Bake at 350° if using a metal pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa and add other ingredients.
Beat until smooth and spread over the marshmallows.

title: mom's cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble up cornbread.
Dry up white bread and break up into little pieces.
Mix in with cornbread.
Beat eggs and mix in. Saute onion and celery in butter until done; add to cornbread mixture.
Add salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and a little sage to taste.
Add turkey or chicken broth; mixture should be moist but not soupy.
Add boiled eggs.
Pour into baking pans and bake at 375° until done.

title: face toast(from kinder-krunchies)
directions: You will need 4 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and mix with oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together and add flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans, filled 2/3 full, one hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: crab pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise and lemon juice; spread on large round platter.
Spread chili sauce on top of cheese mixture (but do not go all the way to the edges). Sprinkle crab on pizza.
Top it off with a few chopped green onion tops.

title: pasta, shrimp and cheese
directions: Cook pasta according to directions and drain.
In a saucepan, saute shrimp and vegetables until tender in butter.
Add salt and oregano.
Keep over low heat.
Add milk and cook for 10 minutes. Now add cheese and mix well.
Add pasta and serve hot.

title: golden scramble
directions: Mix together all cereal and peanuts in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In skillet, melt the margarine and peanut butter. Stir until mixed. Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over cereal.
Mix well.
Put in a 350° oven. Stir 2 or 3 times while in oven. Take out of oven.
Add 1 cup raisins.
Let stand in pan 2 hours before storing.

title: citrus punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a large punch bowl, stirring until all sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Garnish with mint or lemon balm sprigs.
Also, herb sprigs can be frozen in ice cube trays to use in each cup or in punch bowl.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: washboard oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Form into long rolls and refrigerate or freeze until firm.
Slice and bake until golden brown.

title: cherry punch
directions: Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Chill.
Just before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.
Makes 20 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in a large amount of water until tender.
Drain; rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese and add to meat sauce.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half of the meat sauce mixture.
Sprinkle half the Mozzarella cheese over this and then repeat with the noodles, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares. This will allow time for the filling to set slightly.
Makes 15 servings.

title: cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add pineapple syrup, lemon peel, lemon juice and salt to gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in pineapple, celery, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Pour into 5 1/2 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottoms only for 8 medium muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) or line with paper baking cups.
Mix the sugar, vegetable oil, vanilla and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Divide the batter among cups.
Bake 18 to 23 minutes or until golden brown and top springs back when touched lightly.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from cups.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and self-rising flour.
Set aside.
Boil for 1 minute water, butter, oil and cocoa.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar and stir well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rice, cauliflower and broccoli toss
directions: Remove outer green leaves of cauliflower and break cauliflower into flowerets.
Wash thoroughly and set aside.
Remove broccoli stalks and separate broccoli into flowerets; wash thoroughly. Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onions, rice, cheese and bacon; toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently; cover and chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swedish shrimp over rice and peas
directions: Saute onion in oil in a skillet until soft.
Add 3/4 cup of broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until shrimp are pink, about 3 minutes.
Whisk together 1/4 cup of broth, sour cream, mustard and cornstarch until smooth. Whisk into skillet.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add pepper, dill and lemon juice.
Prepare rice and peas; mix together.
Serve shrimp and sauce over rice with peas.

title: grandma's good cream cookies
directions: Roll out on a floured board with your favorite cookie cutter. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; give or take a minute and when cool, add your favorite icing.

title: lollipops
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, and 1/2 c. of water in a saucepan. Set candy thermometer in pan.
Cook without stirring until the thermometer reads 300°.
Add flavoring and coloring, stirring only enough to mix.
If different flavorings and colorings are desired, pour the hot candy into separate warm pans.
Arrange wooden sticks about 2 inches apart in a shallow buttered pan.
Pour a little candy over the top of each stick.
When cold, wrap each lollipop in waxed paper.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: jumbo raisin-nut cookies(old recipe)
directions: Boil water with raisins for 5 minutes. Drain. Measure 1/2 cup of the liquid (add water if needed to make 1/2 cup).
Cool. Stir in soda. Cream the shortening.
Gradually add in sugar mixed with spices.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and raisin liquid.

title: sausage and eggs
directions: Put sausage in crock-pot; add Velveeta.
Scramble eggs, and add to sausage mixture; mix well.
Heat until warm and serve. Note:
Sausage and cheese may be prepared the night before and refrigerated.
Heat 30 to 45 minutes in crock-pot then add scrambled eggs.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together well.
Makes 2 pies.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° until firm.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Mix tomato sauce and tomato paste and set aside.
Mix ground beef, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and egg.
Set aside.
Put water in glass casserole.
Add noodles and microwave 12 to 15 minutes.
Layer, using 1/2 each time:
noodles, cottage cheese mixture, cheese and beef mixture.
Repeat.
Microwave 8 minutes; turn 1/4 of way.
Microwave 8 more minutes.
Turn 1/4 and microwave 6 minutes.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Put Ranch, oil and peppers in a large bowl.
Whisk until well blended.
Pour in crackers and toss until well coated.
Put in a Ziploc bag.
Best after sets for 1 day.
Serve with salad.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburg with onion, drain and season with salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni; mix with pizza sauce, macaroni and hamburg.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Alternate layers with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil. Mix soda into pulp, add to sugar mix.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Add nuts and dates to dry ingredients.
Fold into persimmon mixture.
Pour into oiled pan. Bake 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: punch
directions: Mix and serve cold.

title: vegetarian barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Form into walnut-sized balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Stir together first three ingredients. Press mixture evenly in bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove to a wire rack and cool completely.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook spaghetti in the broth from the chicken.
Add cream of chicken soup to 1 can of water.
Stir in margarine, Ro-Tel and chicken.
Cut cheese in chunks and stir in slowly until melted.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Sort through popcorn and remove all "old maids" and hard kernels.
Melt margarine and marshmallows until well mixed.
In a large pot, mix popcorn, gumdrops, nuts, M&M's and Milk Duds.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn mixture and mix well.
Grease an angel food cake pan well and pour mixture into it.
Press down firmly into pan.
Best results when you let it stand for 24 hours. Turn upside-down and slice.

title: cocoa apple bundt cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oleo and water until fluffy.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.

title: raspberry torte
directions: *We cut it down to slightly over 1 cup to make it less sweet.

title: seafood stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut the eggplant in half, lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out the pulp, leaving the shells intact.
Chop pulp and cook in a small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Saute onion and green pepper in the olive oil until tender.
Remove from heat and add the eggplant, mixing well.
Soak the bread in water. Squeeze water out of the bread and add the bread to the eggplant mixture along with the shrimp, oysters, crabmeat and salt and pepper.
Spoon stuffing evenly into eggplant shell.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs over the top.
Wrap the eggplant in foil and place in a shallow pan.
Pour 1/4 inch hot water into the pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes or until shells are tender.
Makes 2 servings.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Combine next five ingredients and pour over broccoli and cut-up chicken in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: squash or asparagus casserole
directions: Toast the bread and make into fine bread crumbs, preheat the oven to 350°; grate the cheese, melt the butter.
Take 2/3 of the butter and mix it with the crumbs.
Mix the grated cheese with the buttered crumbs, cook the sliced summer squash until lightly done; do not overcook.
Grease the baking dish.
Layer some crumb mixture on the bottom.
Top with a layer of squash (alternate layers of squash and crumb mixture).
Beat the eggs, add the milk, salt, sugar and garlic powder and mix.
Pour over the top of the squash in baking dish.
Pour the other 1/3 of melted butter on top.
Top with a final layer of buttered crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika for the final touch.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Whip Dream Whip; fold in fruit cocktail, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill.
You may add any fresh fruit in season.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in oven on low heat until cheese melts; stir.
Serve on Tostitos.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Mix chopped
apples with sugar; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, add
dry ingredients except nuts together, then add oil, vanilla and
eggs
to
mixture.
Beat
well.
Now
add
apple mixture and nuts and blend together into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured cake
pan
and
bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. When cake is done and cooled, sprinkle powdered sugar sparingly on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together.
Make a well in the dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Pour into 4 small pans or 3 larger ones.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a small bowl, beat together cream cheese, softened margarine and powdered sugar until frothy.
Beat in vanilla. Frost cake as desired.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add picante sauce, soup and chicken broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes and add crawfish tails.
Simmer an additional 20 minutes and serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, pour rice and spread to cover bottom of dish.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix together sour cream and soup.
Spoon over chicken and spread so that it covers the chicken.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over soup and cream mixture. Drizzle butter over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. It is delicious!

title: quick artichoke pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Turn into a large bowl.
Add artichokes and their liquid, mushrooms, cherry tomatoes, olives, parsley and basil.
Toss.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Before serving, season with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into bite-size balls. Place on top of boiler pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Put into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over baked crust.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool and cut.

title: robert redford's favorite dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 8 ounces Cool Whip and spread over crust.
(Spread thick so crust won't break.)
Mix chocolate pudding with 2 cups milk and pour over cream cheese layer.
Mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups milk and pour over chocolate layer.
(Let pudding layers set for a few minutes in refrigerator.)
Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve cold.
May also be frozen for future.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Remove outside leaves; wash cabbage.
Cut into wedges; shred cabbage with knife.
Discard core.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-heat.
Add cabbage, garlic and red pepper.
Sprinkle sugar over cabbage.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add onion and stir-fry 1 minute more or until vegetables are just tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Cook sausage and ground beef until brown.
Drain grease.
Mix Bisquick and cold water until forms a ball.
Divide dough into 2 parts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan and pack.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain excess grease and bake for 30 minutes more.
Drain.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in pan and mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg together.
Sprinkle over fruit; dribble 1/4 pound butter or margarine over top.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: date and nut gems
directions: *If using dates already rolled in sugar, I reduce sugar to 1/3 cup.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Pour drained pineapple into greased casserole dish.
Mix together:
sugar, cheese, flour and pour over pineapple.

title: four layer chocolate nut dessert
directions: Mix well and press into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool before adding second layer.

title: steak and pepper sandwiches
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and oregano in oil over medium-high heat 3 to 4 minutes. Remove and keep warm. Add beef to pan and fry until cooked. Return vegetables to pan and stir to combine. Remove from heat and place equal amounts of beef mixture on bottom half of each roll. Close sandwiches.

title: granville torte
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, Crisco and beaten yolks.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased and floured pans.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding 1 cup sugar until stiff.
Spread over cake mixture in pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hoot and poopers
directions: Run first 3 ingredients through blender with enough water to mix.
Put in gallon jar and add cherry vodka.
Fill jar the rest of the way with water.
Mix 2/3 of the mix with one-third 7-Up.

title: graham cracker nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake(fruit cake)
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Mix in order given.
Bake in floured and greased tube cake pan at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until done.
Cake can be baked slower.
It is moist and weighs about 5 pounds.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla; mix again.
Spread on cooled crust and decorate with pecan halves.

title: bleeding heart jello(for halloween)
directions: You will also need a 1 gallon food storage bag (plain, no zip close) and a 6 1/2-cup heart-shaped Jell-O mold or cake pan.

title: mushroom chicken(serves four)
directions: Take chicken and place into 10 or 12-inch baking pan with cover.
Season with seasoned salt and garlic (both sides).
Add cream of mushroom soup, then cream of chicken soup.
Blend lightly.
Add mushroom pieces to cover mixture.
Then add fried onions.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken falls off bone.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: marinated grilled zucchini(yields 4 servings)
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise.
Pour dressing about 1 1/2-inches high in a lasagna type pan.
Put zucchini in skin side up.
Let soak for 2 hours.
Heat grill on medium.
Put zucchini skin side down and cook for 30 minutes or until fork goes through easily. Salt and pepper to taste.
Enjoy!

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: In medium-size bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and stir until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with chilled cherry pie filling before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all together well.
Form into balls about the walnut size. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with floured bottom of glass.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown at edges.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Layer bottom of pie shell with butterscotch sauce.
Mix together pudding mix and cold milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and 6 chopped candy bars.
Pour in pie shell.
Garnish top of pie with last candy bar.
Freeze 6 hours before serving.

title: economic casserole
directions: Note: May add 1 can of mushrooms, if it is within your budget.

title: pear honey
directions: Shred pears, not too small, or cut small with knife.
Cook pears, sugar, pineapple and lemon on medium heat until the juice gets clear looking and boiling.
Put into jars and seal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together thoroughly all ingredients except the squash. Then add squash and bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and put in ice cream freezer. Finish filling with milk. Freeze and enjoy.

title: angel flake biscuits *
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in the 1/4 cup lukewarm water; cut in cold butter.
Mix with buttermilk.
Roll out, cut and bake at 400°.

title: sugar 'n spice snack
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Grease jelly roll pans.
Mix corn snack and nuts in large bowl.
Beat orange juice and egg whites in a small bowl with wire whisk or hand beater until foamy.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Stir into corn snack mixture until well coated.
Spread in pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes, until light brown and crisp.
Cool and store in airtight container.
(Fewer than 200 calories.)

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water; cook to 220°.
Add peanuts and butter and cook to 298°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda, stirring thoroughly. Pour onto large, buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Use as many chicken pieces as you will eat.
You can skin the chicken or leave it as is.
Dip chicken in melted butter.
Roll chicken pieces in a mixture of herb seasoned stuffing mix, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Place chicken pieces in greased shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 2.

title: buttermilk coffee cake(no eggs - crumb)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cut butter with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs and to this add 1 teaspoon cinnamon, set aside.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add buttermilk and vanilla to remaining crumb mixture, stirring just enough to moisten (by hand).
Spread batter in greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt the sugar in the vinegar.
Add paste, soy sauce, ginger and juice from fruit.
Adjust sauce adding more sugar or vinegar to taste.
Add meatballs to the sauce and heat to medium high, stirring frequently as the sauce thickens.
When thickened, add chunks and cherries, peppers and onions.
Stir to coat and turn into chafing dish.

title: shrimpys
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on English muffins. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Cut in quarters and serve.

title: pea salad
directions: Break lettuce and line a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix peas, onion, bell pepper and Sweet 'N Low together.
Sprinkle over lettuce and top with mayonnaise, cheese and bacon bits.
Let set at least 1 hour before serving.

title: aunt millie's ham loaf
directions: Mix the two meats together thoroughly; add the remaining ingredients.
Place in baking pans that have been greased or spread with Pam.
Pour glaze over loaves.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°. Baste with glaze every 10 minutes for another 45 to 60 minutes. Makes 2 nice-sized loaves or ham-meat balls.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter and pour into pan.
Make batter with next 3 ingredients and pour over butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini-tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Saute zucchini in butter with a very light sprinkling of garlic powder. Layer zucchini, tomatoes, onions and mushrooms in 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add pecans, vanilla, water and flour.
Mix well. Shape dough in small balls or fingers.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake in slow oven at 300° to 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Use loaf of bread that's 2 or 3 days old.
Freeze.
Cut crust off bread.
Cut center into strips about 1/2-inch wide.
Lay sticks on cookie sheet (do not stack on top of each other).
Break crust up and put in separate pan.
Put all bread in oven at 200° until completely dried out (turn occasionally).
Take crust and crushed in blender.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix the peanut butter, Crisco oil and 1/2 cup sugar.
Dip sticks in mixture.
Let extra mixture drip off.
Roll in bread crumbs.

title: machate
directions: Brown the ground beef and peppers.
In	large bowl, mix tomato soup,
mushroom soup, water, mushrooms, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper.

title: aunt tony's mustard sauce
directions: Mix all together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: peanut butter rounds
directions: Spread peanut butter between crackers; this will make 33 cookies.
Melt the package of almond bark in double boiler.
When smooth and creamy, dip the cookies in with thongs and place on wax paper to dry and harden.
Can also be used to dip pretzels or make peanut clusters.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, syrup and oil.
Beat well. Dissolve soda in cold water.
Add the rest of the ingredients except the hot water.
Blend well.
Add hot water.
Mixture will be thin, it makes a big batch.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Stir in peanut butter and milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into two 9-inch graham cracker pie crusts. Freeze. Then take out and cut and let stand 10 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, chili sauce, green pepper, onion and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly. Makes 4 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add the tomatoes, dressing and the Doritos to the salad just before serving.
Makes a large salad.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and soft butter.
Beat all together, then add corn meal, vinegar, milk and salt.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour or until consistency of Jell-O.

title: sausage-cheese egg bake
directions: Fry sausage until crumbly and brown; drain well.
Add all ingredients except onions; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 onions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: cuban green beans
directions: Cook beans quickly until tender, not over cooked; add rest of ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Beat butter, sugar and egg in a large bowl until fluffy.
Combine banana and milk in a bowl. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt onto wax paper.
Stir into sugar mixture alternately with banana-milk mixture.
Stir in nuts. Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool in pan on wire rack 5 minutes.
Turn out of pan.
Cool completely.
(Can be frozen.)

title: humitas(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Combine corn and milk.
Blend on high speed 30 seconds.
Add eggs, paprika, salt and pepper.
Blend 15 seconds longer until smooth.
In heavy 10-inch skillet, melt butter on moderate heat. When foam subsides, add onions and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring until soft, not brown.
Pour in corn.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered.
Stir frequently 5 to7 minutes until thickens somewhat.
Stir in cheese.
As soon as it melts, remove from heat. Can be wrapped in corn husks; steam like tamales.

title: chicken breasts with pineapple
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour to coat. Cook chicken in oil in skillet until tender; drain.
Arrange pineapple slices on chicken breasts.
Melt margarine in saucepan; stir in cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: fruits cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils thoroughly.
Put them in a saucepan with the water; cover and cook over low heat 2 hours or until tender.
Melt butter in a skillet; add garlic and onion; saute 10 minutes.
Put into saucepan with lentils, curry powder, salt, pepper and chicken stock.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Each serving contains 125 calories.

title: pat's cheese ball
directions: Mix
well.
Form balls.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill. Roll in chopped pecans.	Slice and serve as on crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend Cool Whip and cream cheese together first.
Blend everything else.
Put in a dish (clay pot preferred).
Refrigerate. Place gummy worms in pot to decorate.

title: mistakes
directions: Brown sausage and hamburg; drain off excess grease.
Add cubed Velveeta and cook until cheese is melted.
Add spices; stir well. Spread on slices of party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel
and
wash
potatoes; slice and cook until tender. Cream potatoes,
sugar,
butter
and eggs; add vanilla, salt, baking powder,
milk
and	flour.	Bake in 9-inch pie shell at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: lindberg relish
directions: Grind all vegetables in food chopper; add salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain and mix with the remaining ingredients.
Requires no cooking.
Does not have to be sealed.
Use in salads with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Stir in green beans, tomato soup, water, salt and pepper; turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salad oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
In a separate bowl, sift the flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix with liquids.
Add nuts.
Bake in 3 greased 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 3 loaves. This is good with cream cheese filling.

title: mom's fruitcake cookies
directions: Put first
five ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix flour and baking
powder
over these ingredients and mix well.
Pour condensed milk
over these and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased
cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: ricotta cheese, onion and parsley frittata
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Beat in Ricotta cheese and parsley.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter with oil in a heavy 8 or 10-inch skillet.
When butter foams, add onion. Saute over medium heat until pale yellow.
Remove onion with a slotted spoon.
Stir into egg mixture.

title: corn bread "stuff"
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion, using 2 tablespoons oil.

title: naomi's corn li-bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Line two loaf pans with wax paper.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: apple snacks
directions: Cut each crescent roll triangle into 2 to 3 pieces.
Cut and peel apple into 8 pieces.
Roll pieces in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Wrap pieces with crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes (or as specifies on roll package).

title: peach cream
directions: Soften gelatin in liquid until dissolved.
Mix in lemon juice, peaches, sugar, extract and herbs.
Chill until thick but not set. Fold in whipped topping and pour into a one quart mold or six individual molds.
Chill until set.

title: cheese boxes
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat with a mixer until creamy.
Spread on all sides of 1-inch cubes of bread.
Sprinkle with more paprika and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: soft sugar cookie
directions: Beat
eggs
and add sugar, shortening, nutmeg and salt. Add baking
soda
to
3 cups of the flour and add to mixture. Add remaining
2 cups flour alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well. Roll out and cut.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: baked stuffed chicken breasts
directions: In nonstick skillet, heat 1 teaspoon margarine until bubbly. Add mushrooms, onion, vermouth or water, garlic, salt and pepper. Saute until onion is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in rice. Place chicken breasts, skin side down, and spread half of rice mixture onto each.
