Fold long sides over then roll breast from short end to enclose filling.
Secure with wooden toothpick. Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt remaining margarine.
Roll each stuffed breast in margarine then in bread crumbs coating all sides.
Spray baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Transfer chicken rolls to dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove toothpicks before serving.
Contains 310 calories per serving, 7 g. fat.
Yield:
2 servings per recipe.

title: vanilla crisps
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
These may be rolled out to cut into Christmas shapes and decorated with icing and sprinkles.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Pour off fat.
Blend pizza sauce, garlic salt and oregano with the browned ground beef. Put mixture in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan (or a jelly roll pan). Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
In a small bowl mix the eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour.
Pour mixture over the meat and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Mushrooms, bell peppers, sausage or Canadian bacon may be added with the Mozzarella cheese.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, pepper, milk and oleo.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and wrap in foil and bake until very tender. While potatoes are baking, saute seasonings in butter.
Add seasoned shrimp
(and crabmeat) and cook about 10 minutes longer. Add cheese and melt.
Scoop out potatoes while they are hot and mash thoroughly.
Add shrimp mixture and mix well.
Add milk to get the desired consistency.
Season to taste.
Stuff potato mixture back into shells and top with grated cheese.
Bake before serving
at 350 degrees until hot.
These may be frozen before baking.

title: pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time and mix well after each egg.
Add baking soda to 1/2 cup buttermilk and mix well.
Add to creamed butter, sugar and eggs. Add flour and rest of buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla extract and then fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 9 pan.

title: underwood picnic dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, deviled ham, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper until smooth.
Stir in green pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: fresh lime pie
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, beat egg yolks with electric beater for about 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Add condensed milk, lime zest, lime juice, and food color;
beat until smooth.
Turn into baked pie shell, spreading evenly.
(Filling will be soft.)

title: butterscotch crisp
directions: Melt peanut butter and morsels over low heat and pour over Chinese noodles (2-5 oz. cans), Cornflakes or pretzels.

title: tuna cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together, except chopped nuts.
Roll balls in nuts.
Allow to set for several hours.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain. Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer half meat mixture, top with half chips, then cheese.
Repeat meat, chips
and cheese layer.
Use 2-quart casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.
May use 2 cups cooked chicken, instead of beef.

title: dutch shortbread
directions: Mix by hand butter and sugar; add flour.
Mix very good by hand.
Butter the pan lightly (9 x 13-inch).
Press dough in pan. Prick it with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour or until done. Cut right away.
Let cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes in greased muffin pan.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup flour and salad dressing to make a paste. Spread mixture all over chicken pieces to coat. Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: baked lentils
directions: Combine lentils, water and bay leaf in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, lower heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Drain. Put lentils in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: white bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add 4 cups flour.
Mix well and add the rest of the flour.
It's best if not too stiff. Leave a little sticky.

title: mexican meatball casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix ground beef, hard-cooked eggs, 1/4 cup onion, parsley, cinnamon, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into 1 inch balls; place in ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2 inches.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes or until meatballs are brown.

title: eagle brand milk(homemade)
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Makes 1 1/2 cups or equal to 1 can.

title: hearty cabbage soup
directions: For crockery cooking be sure to slice vegetables thin in all crock-pot recipes unless otherwise instructed.
Meat cooks faster than veggies in a crock-pot.
Always put veggie on bottom and meat on top.

title: egg bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread croutons in pan.
Brown sausage; spread over croutons.
Mix soup, milk and eggs.
Pour over sausage and croutons.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Let set for 30 minutes before baking for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top; bake until cheese melts.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and boil about 3 minutes. Pack pickles solidly into clean jars.
Add 1 tsp. salt and 1/2 onion sliced to each qt.
Cover with boiling syrup and seal at once.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Blend all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Use 1/2 cup of mix per mug and add hot water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except chipped beef. Chop it fine into small pieces. Fold in. Will shape into ball easier after being in refrigerator for awhile.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all together except chocolate chips.
Pour into a pan and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: apple dip
directions: Cream together sugars and cream cheese.
Add vanilla.
Crush peanuts and mix in.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Use equal amounts of ham and cheese.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat until well blended.
Spread mixture on cut surfaces of rolls.
Add ham and cheese slices. Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, forming into a ball.
Can be chilled overnight to blend flavors.
This recipe is easily doubled or more to make a larger batch.

title: jean's delicious spinach
directions: Mix well spinach, mushroom soup, cream cheese and onions. Pour into a baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers mixed with oleo.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: recipe for preserving children
directions: Mix the children with the dogs and cats, then empty into the field, stirring continuously.
Sprinkle the field with the flowers.
Pour the brook gently over the pebbles.
Cover all with the deep blue sky and bake in the hot sun.
When the children are well browned, they may be removed.
You will now find that they are ready to be set in a bath tub to cool.

title: ham and cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill and serve with chips and crackers.

title: sweet paulette's chocolate surprise
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Grease and flour oblong cake pan.
Cover bottom with pecans.
Pour cake mix over pecans. Mix last 3 ingredients together and spoon over cake mix.

title: addie's egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and scalded milk slowly.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in moderate oven 25 to 30 minutes.
The custard is done when a knife put in center comes out clean.

title: sky-high biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add milk, stir quickly and briefly with fork.
Add more milk or flour, if needed.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll or pat gently to 1-inch thickness. Cut into biscuits.
Place on biscuit pan so edges are just touching.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute celery in butter until tender; add drained corn (keep 2 tablespoons of liquid) and heat until warmed through.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and reserved corn liquid and fold into corn mixture.
Place turkey in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with corn mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 15 minutes in 350°.

title: john bengetty
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green pepper.
Mix in corn, mushrooms, pimentos, soups and egg noodles.
Layer in casserole dish with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until hot and cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: african chow mein
directions: Brown meat; add rest of the ingredients.
Bake in covered and greased casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill.

title: pork chop thing
directions: Coat pork chops in lemon pepper.
Brown.
Reduce heat.
Mix Port wine and water. Pour over meat.
Simmer 30 minutes or until liquid reduces.
(Turn twice while cooking.)

title: chinese-style cabbage
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Drop in vegetables; stir well.
Cover tightly.
Steam 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring several times. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Serves four.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Line bottom of baking dish with rice.
Prepare broccoli according to package directions; place on top of rice.
Pour 1/3 soup and mayonnaise over rice and broccoli.
Layer chicken on top of this and top with the remainder of soup and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over this and then top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together.
Grease either a Bundt pan or angel food cake pan with margarine or butter.
Mix 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and 2 teaspoons of sugar.
Splash over greased pan.
Pour in cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan when cooled.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with margarine in bottom of pan (11 x 9). Save 1/2 cup of Oreos for garnish. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on top of Oreos. Mix condensed milk and regular milk to make 3 cups. Add to pudding mix and beat until thick. Pour over cream cheese mix. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and garnish with Oreos.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish, depending upon how much you wish to bake.
Salt and pepper.
Place sliced cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir soup and add a very small amount of water.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with crumbs and drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Another quick, easy recipe for working gals!

title: cheese balls
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in cheese, flour and pepper.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Crumble cheese crackers until fine; roll the balls in the crumbs and deep fry until golden.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Let cool.
Cut cake into regular serving pieces.
Puncture a hole in each square.
Fill the holes with chocolate syrup.

title: pasta with shrimp and broccoli
directions: Saute shrimp in medium-high skillet with oil until pink and half done, about 2 minutes.
Add garlic, pepper flakes, parsley and salt. Toss. Add broccoli; toss to coat.
Add liquids and toss again. Add pasta and toss well. Salt and pepper and toss with Parmesan cheese. Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: quick mix cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add sugar, Crisco and egg.
Mix milk and vanilla; add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts, coconut and cherries, then drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: margaret's rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bake at 325°.
Stir once in a while.
Add the vanilla when you take from oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until thick.

title: grandma, florence best's refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and dates.
Combine with first mixture.
Divide into two parts; shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Slice and bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and press into (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Beat with mixer the next 4 ingredients to form thick custard. Blend into custard Dream Whip, nuts and pineapple.
Cut bananas lengthwise.
Then in layers alternate custard mix and banana slices onto graham crust.
Top with crushed nuts and maraschino cherries. Chill 8 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli.
Cook as directed.
Put in baking dish. Pour mixture over.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: crock-pot corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high 2 hours.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix all ingredients a little at a time, except powdered sugar. Stir and mix until all are mixed well.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
No cooking.
They are ready to eat. Will keep in fridge for sometime.

title: seafood salad
directions: Toss fish together and chill.
Add celery, olives and rice. Mix salad dressing and lemon juice.
Toss everything together.

title: italian sliced tomatoes(a treat with any meal)
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/8 inch thick.
On a large plate, lay slices to cover the total plate.
Take pure olive oil and splash all tomatoes.
Take lemon juice or white vinegar and splash slices lightly.
Sprinkle coarse black pepper, garlic salt, oregano and sweet basil; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425° in muffin pans (greased).

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg, buttermilk and flour, then vanilla.
Place in refrigerator for a few hours.
Then roll and cut out cookies.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 - 15 minutes or until tops are beginning to brown.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Age 2 weeks.
Place 1 package cream cheese on plate.
Pour Jezebel Sauce over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: marshmallow peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in saucepan.
Cook until the soft ball stage (234°).
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Cook in a greased cake pan at 375° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut beef
and
pork into small cubes.
Salt and pepper. Brown in	small amount of fat.
Add chopped onions and celery. Then add gravy, molasses and chop suey sauce.
Cook until meat is tender. Thicken with flour.
Add bean sprouts.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash and mix with mixer the soup, sour cream, onion, squash, salt and pepper; set aside.
Mix Stove Top with a little butter and put 1/2 in the bottom of a casserole dish; pour the mixture in and add the other 1/2 of Stove Top.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: fruit and cheese kabobs
directions: Peel and trim eyes from pineapple; remove core.
Cut pineapple into 1-inch pieces.
Thread cheese cubes, pineapple and strawberries on 40 (6-inch) bamboo skewers.

title: taco pie
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning, black olives and 1/4 to 1/2 cup water.
Lay crescent rolls or pizza crust in bottom of 9-inch glass pan and spread half of finely crushed Doritos chips on it.
Pour hamburger mix over, then layer on sour cream, grated cheese and remainder of Doritos chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chris' cold fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in a bowl.
In a separate bowl mix all other ingredients.
Add melted butter and mix well with hands.
Form balls.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Cook lasagna as directed on package.
Brown ground meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat and simmer.
In a Pyrex (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan, layer sauce, lasagna and cheese until full (approximately 3 layers).
Top with cheese and bake for approximately 30 to 45 minutes or until center is hot.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork and then pour in Pet milk.
Stir well. Then melt margarine, add cocoa, mix together well, then add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.
If you don't want thick pies, it will make 3.

title: spaghetti in garlic sauce
directions: Melt together olive oil and butter until warm, not hot.
Saute garlic for 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and parsley. Simmer 5 minutes.
Toss with cooked spaghetti.

title: stromboli
directions: Grease bread loaves and let rise. Cut in half and spread flat with hands.
Fill with what you desire.
Fold all four sides together and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix the oil, sugar, eggs and pulp.
Sift the flour, baking powder, nutmeg, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add the pecans. Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 75 minutes in a tube pan. Test with a toothpick.

title: hello dollies(very rich cookie)
directions: Melt butter in a 1 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Sprinkle other ingredients in layers, then pour sweetened condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool, then cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: graham muffins
directions: Mix together; add enough white flour to mix well.
Pour into muffin tins (greased).
Bake at 400° until raised and golden.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions in a large pot.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, liquid from kidney beans and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans and simmer 15 minutes or desired consistency.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in Ranch dressing in a Ziploc bag.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown and crispy.

title: quick chicken
directions: Place in roasting pan. Pour water over chicken (about 1/4 inch) to keep moist. Put foil over pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Boil noodles, strain.
Add margarine (fat-free) and Parmesan cheese; mix together.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix pie filing and almond extract.
Place in oven 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Mix baking mix, sugar, milk and butter with fork to soft dough; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Stir in almonds.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Serve on rolls.

title: franks and crescents
directions: Fill each wiener with cheese strip.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place wiener on wide end of triangle; roll up. Place on greased cookie sheet, cheese side up.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until rolls are golden brown.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar well.
Boil water and Sure-Jell for 1 minute; mix with berries and stir for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Stir again before putting in jars.
Store in freezer.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiled water.
Mix sugar in water and stir. Add cold water and juices.
Pour in a half gallon carton and freeze.
When frozen, put in refrigerator about 1 hour before using.
Put in punch bowl and add ginger ale; mix.
Add frozen strawberries and mash in with a potato masher.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until almost tender. Drain. In separate pan, saute onions and peppers in butter until tender. Add to cabbage. Stir in cheese and add 1 1/2 cups crushed croutons. Transfer to greased 9 x 13 dish. Pour milk over top. Do not stir. Sprinkle with remaining croutons. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Refrigerate until cool and serve.

title: seven layer cake
directions: Put melted oleo and graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan; press down.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, peanut butter chips, nuts and coconut.
Pat down.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: glory morning muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, coconut and pecans. In separate bowl, combine eggs, oil, apple and vanilla; add to flour mixture.
Stir until combined.
Spoon into greased or lined muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
These freeze very well.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Stir in milk gradually.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly until thick and boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir 1/2 hot mixture into egg yolks; add to mixture in pan.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Press plastic wrap onto filling.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, no longer than 48.
Remove plastic; top with whip cream.

title: royal icing
directions: Mix together until icing consistency.

title: parmesan catfish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large ziptop plastic bag. Add fillets; seal bag and shake to coat fillets with cheese mixture.
Place on broiler pan coated with cooking spray; discard remaining cheese mixture.
Broil 3 inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Contains 148 calories.

title: golden potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
In a saucepan combine milk, shortening and potatoes.
Cook and stir over low heat, just until shortening melts.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Mix together sour cream, pudding mix and milk.
Cut cake in small pieces.
(I slice and cut each piece in half.)

title: groundnut stew
directions: In large skillet, heat the 3 tablespoons of oil.
Add the beef.
While browning, add the nutmeg and chili powder.
When meat is browned, add the onions, garlic, tomato paste, water and pepper.
Simmer until meat is tender.
A half hour before serving, heat the peanut butter and remaining oil in small saucepan.
Stir over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter mixture slowly to beef stew; simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage until browned in a large Dutch oven. Drain all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Add green pepper, onion and garlic. Cook until tender. Add flour and blend. Stir in tomatoes, water and parsley. Bring to a boil. Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Return to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Add shrimp. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine the butter and onion.
Add the cream cheese, Velveeta cheese and milk; melt slowly.
Add the cream of chicken soup.
Use same water from broccoli; add 3/4 cup to soup.
Heat slowly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and remove seed.
Set seed aside.
Mash avocados and add lemon or lime juice.
Stir in other ingredients.
Place seed in center of dish to prevent browning.

title: gougere
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Place water, butter, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Heat until butter is melted and mix is boiling rapidly.
Add flour to butter; mix all at once.
Continue cooking.
Stir until mix forms a ball and leaves sides of pan clean.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix well between each egg.
Stir in all but 1 tablespoon gougere.
Place rounded tablespoons of dough on sheet in ring shape about 8 to 9-inches round.
Leave about 2 1/2 inches space in the middle.
Sprinkle dough with rest of cheese.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet 'n sour peglegs
directions: Early in the day, combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Chill 2 to 8 hours.
Just before serving, microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serve with party picks. Yields 12 Peglegs.

title: appetizer ham chunks
directions: Combine chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Make sure all jelly is combined with chili sauce.
Cut 48 cubes about 3/4-inch each from the ham.
Serve with toothpicks for dipping ham in sauce.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: stir-fried asparagus
directions: Dip asparagus into large pot of salted boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain.
Then put asparagus into basin of icy water. When cool, pat dry.
Toast sesame seed until slightly brown.

title: rolled oats yeast bread
directions: Scald milk and butter; add to oats and let cool.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, flour and vanilla.
Melt oleo and cocoa and add to egg-flour mixture.
Add pecan pieces.
Pour into greased 8 x 14-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When done, remove from oven.
Place marshmallow halves on top of cooked cake.
Ice.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar, flour and onion in a bowl. Add egg and milk. Stir until thick. Drop by heaping teaspoonful into hot deep fryer (375°), frying only a few at a time.
Fry until a golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Great with fish.

title: creamy macaroni and ham bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner; add ham, sour cream, onion, mustard and caraway seed.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbs and drizzle with margarine. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: momma's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat in large bowl.
Add salt and pepper for taste, catsup, eggs and onion.
Mix well.
Add crackers and shape in large baking pan.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain off excess grease.
Pour remaining ingredients over meat loaf.
Return to oven until done about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lo-cal easy jello salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: butter ball chiffons(cookies)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; then mix separate the last 3 ingredients.
Cut toffee candy into small pieces or run through blender.
Mix lightly the two groups of ingredients.
With hand form dough into small balls or patties.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: orange mold
directions: Mix Jell-O and water until dissolved.
Add rest and mix well. Pour into a bowl or mold.

title: cabbage slaw dressing
directions: Bring to a boil.
While hot, add 3 tablespoons margarine. Cool and pour over shredded cabbage.
Serve cold.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Boil together Lipton onion soup, cream of chicken soup and water.
Pour mixture over chicken and rice. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sizzling chicken fajitas
directions: Saute the pepper, onion and chicken in the olive oil over medium heat for 5 minutes or until the chicken is just done.
Add the fajita seasoning and lime juice and heat through for 3 minutes.

title: mamaw h's miracle whip cake
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, sugar and vanilla.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients and alternately add water and dry ingredients to Miracle Whip mixture, stirring well after each addition.
Pour in lightly greased and floured pans (two 8-inch or 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use toothpick test to determine if done.
Allow to cool and remove and frost with creamy cocoa frosting.

title: angel food pineapple trifle
directions: Cut angel food cake into 2-inch cubes; set aside.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix pudding, 1/2 cup pineapple juice and milk.
Beat 2 minutes, until thickened; add pineapple.
Stir in sour cream until well blended.
Place 1/3 cake in bowl; drizzle 2 to 3 tablespoons pineapple juice over cake.
Spoon 1/3 cup pudding mixture over cake.
Repeat, ending with pudding mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: fudge (no cook)
directions: Mix together and press in pan.
Refrigerate and cut.
(I've added 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of peanut butter and it works fine for variety.)
